"Arbeidstilsynet har avsl\u00e5tt s\u00f8knaden om samtykke fra ARCTIC CENTER AS ang\u00e5ende et tiltak i Troms\u00f8, da de ikke har dokumentert at kravene til blant annet bygningsareal, ventilasjon og helse- og sikkerhetsforhold er oppfylt. De m\u00e5 ogs\u00e5 betale et gebyr og har mulighet til \u00e5 klage p\u00e5 vedtaket. Arbeidsgiver m\u00e5 informere arbeidsmilj\u00f8utvalget, verneombudet eller ansattes representant om avslaget.A note is attached regarding Arctic Center's handling of exemptions related to the building permit for Plan ID 1875. Feedback on the progress of the case is requested from the recipients. - Erik Joachimsen, CEO of Arctic Center AS.Ny s\u00f8knad om etablering av skianlegget \"Arctic Center\" p\u00e5 Kval\u00f8ya i Troms\u00f8 er sendt p\u00e5 ny h\u00f8ring etter justeringer. S\u00f8knaden inneholder flere planlagte tiltak og dispensasjoner fra fire planbestemmelser. Kommunen ber om rask tilbakemelding og foresl\u00e5r fire dispensasjoner som forventes \u00e5 bli godkjent. Andre myndigheter har fire uker til \u00e5 fatte avgj\u00f8relse eller avgi uttalelse. Vedleggene best\u00e5r av en rekke dokumenter og informasjon til de ulike involverte parter.Andrea Schneider confirms receipt of a neighbor notice regarding plans for water and sewage pipelines in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn near Troms\u00f8. The plans include building VAO pipelines from Eidkjosen to H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn and a road in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn, with consideration for future development in the tourism facility. The development is divided into three phases, but only two are described in detail. Schneider, being the owner of Straumsvegen 536, is a close neighbor affected by the activities and will review the plans with Kjell Hermod Strandli.\n\nPersonen sender en e-post for \u00e5 klage p\u00e5 fristen for \u00e5 svare p\u00e5 informasjon om graving av en ledning i strandsonen. De mener at fristen p\u00e5 fire arbeidsdager er for kort og ber om en forlengelse til uke 19 p\u00e5 grunn av et langt forskningstokt til Polhavet uten tilgang til internett. De ber ogs\u00e5 om mer detaljert informasjon om hvor dypt ledningen vil bli gravd ned eller spylt ned. En annen person bekrefter mottak av klagen og sier at de vil se p\u00e5 den sammen med en annen person.\n\nThe email is a response to a neighbor notification regarding plans for a water and sewage pipeline in H\u00e4kybotn near Troms0. The sender, as the owner of Straumsvegen 536, feels they should have been informed earlier and requests an extension on the response deadline due to scheduling conflicts. They also question the specifics of how the pipeline will be installed in the area and raise concerns about potential quick clay in the area.\n\nIt is essential to thoroughly investigate and map the presence of quick clay in the area where excavation is planned in order to prevent or compensate for possible damage to buildings and roads. Concerns are raised about the lack of information on private water wells in the area, including a privately owned drinking water well on Straumsvegen 534 that is not documented in the investigation. It is unclear how the quality of drinking water will be guaranteed during or after excavation when the location of private water wells is uncertain. In the development plan, only two out of three phases are described in detail, with questions raised about the purpose of the remaining capacity for future expansion and the potential development of a prohibited cabin village. Additionally, there is no information on who will cover the costs for connecting affected landowners with the VAO pipeline.\n\nThe writer suspects that the project is planned at the expense of the residents of H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn, with the aim of obtaining additional financial support from them due to potential water issues caused by the construction project. Concerns are raised about the visibility of pipelines during low tide, the presence of quick clay in the area, and the lack of information on private water wells that may be affected by the project. The writer also questions how the quality of drinking water will be guaranteed during and after construction. Additionally, the plan outlines three development phases.\n\nBeskrivelsen inkluderer to faser av et utbyggingsprosjekt, hvor fase 1 er oppstarten og fase 2 inkluderer hotell, leiligheter og kafeteria. Det er ogs\u00e5 nevnt en restkapasitet for framtidig utvidelse med 600 personer. Sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5let er hva denne kapasiteten og fase 3 av utviklingen vil inneb\u00e6re. Det reises bekymring for om VAO-ledningen m\u00e5 dimensjoneres for fremtidig utbygging med en hytteby, selv om det ikke er tillatt \u00e5 bygge en slik by. Det diskuteres ogs\u00e5 tilkoblingsmuligheter og hvem som skal betale for disse, samt bekymringer knyttet til synligheten av ledningene ved ilandf\u00f8ring.\n\nAndrea Schneider raises concerns about the impact of development on the natural habitat and wildlife in the Mammakjosen area, particularly on the bird reserve and marine mammals. She questions how these ecosystems will be protected from disturbances caused by alterations to water flow in the rivers and additional noise pollution from construction. Schneider also emphasizes the need for respect towards landowners in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn and a consideration of the effects of climate change on the region.\n\nThe email discusses concerns regarding a project related to water and sewage pipelines in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn near Troms\u00f8. The impact on the nature reserve, birds, fish, and mammals in the area is highlighted, with a focus on potential disturbances to the ecosystem and stress caused by additional noise from laying the pipelines. The sender requests guarantees that the project will not disrupt the ecosystem and urges careful consideration of the potential consequences on the wildlife in the area.\n\nAndrea Schneider expresses concern over the impact of construction on wildlife such as moose, reindeer, and sheep in the Mammakjosen, Srbotn, H\u00e4kybotn, and surrounding areas. She emphasizes the need for minimal disturbance to wildlife as well as respectful treatment of landowners in H\u00e5 k\u00f8ybotn and the environment. Schneider also highlights the importance of preserving nature, especially in light of climate change. She urges for a reevaluation of construction plans to prioritize the preservation of nature over increased development.\n\nAndrea is reminding the sender to take into account upcoming holidays when planning for the water and sewage pipeline project in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn. She expresses concern about the short timeframe between receiving information and the departure date. The sender assures Andrea that the pipeline work will be done underground and will not have a major impact on the surrounding area.\n\nI forbindelse med detaljprosjektering vil det blir gjort unders\u00f8kelser og prosjektering for \u00e5 sikre de lokale naturressursene. SWECO har lang erfaring med denne type problemstillinger. Det er gitt en utsatt frist for merknad, og det oppfordres til \u00e5 sende inn merknaden s\u00e5 snart som mulig. Andrea Schneider informerer om at hun vil sende inn merknad, men p\u00e5peker at tidsrammen er kort med bare 4 arbeidsdager mellom informasjon og avreise.\n\nAndrea Schneider is concerned about a water and sewage pipeline construction project near her property in H\u00e4k\u00f8ybotn, Troms. She has not received any information or a neighbor notification about the project and is requesting to be informed in the same way as other affected neighbors. She will be on a research expedition during the normal response period for neighbor notifications and asks for an extension. The project coordinator reassures her that the construction will not have a significant impact on the terrain and that measures will be taken to protect local natural resources.The Sami Parliament (S\u00e1mediggi) in \u00c1vjov\u00e1rgeaidnu provides a statement regarding the establishment of the \"Arctic Center\" ski resort in Troms\u00f8 municipality. They express concerns about Sami cultural heritage and the impact on reindeer husbandry. After a site inspection revealed 46 automatic protected Sami cultural monuments, the Sami Parliament initially had reservations about the project. However, with further details on the water pipeline construction method that minimizes disturbance to the terrain and nearby cultural heritage sites, they now believe there is minimal risk of conflict with the protected cultural monument. The Sami Parliament has no further cultural heritage objections to the project.Lone Alien H\u00f8gda requested an extension for a dispensation for the establishment of a ski center in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn on Kval\u00f8ya. Thea Solvoll Liahjell granted the extension until May 24, 2023.Anders Koller Tufte is inquiring about the deadline for feedback on a recent hearing related to the Arctic. He asks if any responses have been received and inquires about the progress of the processing of the matter. Anders Koller Tufte is an architect at Ihuga AS.Hilgunn Angvik received a neighbor notification regarding the Arctic Center project, expressing concern about the lack of proper communication and consultation regarding the potential impacts on their property and neighboring properties. They are particularly worried about potential risks, such as landslides, and question the rushed nature of the project. They also raise concerns about the proposed water pipeline and potential disruptions to their water sources. Angvik requests transparent treatment of the water pipeline issue and proper consideration for landowners involved.Troms Fylkeskommune har mottatt en s\u00f8knad om etablering av skianlegget \"Arctic Center\" i H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn fra Troms\u00f8 kommune. Saken gjelder oppdatering av en tidligere s\u00f8knad, med endringer i prosjektet. Fylkeskommunen har uttalt bekymring ang\u00e5ende nedbygging av myromr\u00e5der og oppfordrer til \u00e5 vurdere avb\u00f8tende tiltak og naturrestaurering. Det er ogs\u00e5 diskusjon om dispensasjonss\u00f8knader og kollektivtransport i forbindelse med anlegget. Fylkeskommunen vurderer \u00e5 p\u00e5klage en eventuell dispensasjon og oppfordrer til videre dialog med relevant personell.Anders Koller Tufte sent an email to Thea Solvoll Liahjell and Erik regarding the Arctic Center permit application. Thea thanked Anders for the offer and said they would contact him if they need further information. Anders had previously asked if they had reviewed the revised application materials and suggested meeting next week to discuss.Anders Koller Tufte has sent a response to Troms\u00f8 kommune regarding the building application for Arctic Center Phase 1. They are withdrawing the application for a new top cafe and related dispensations. They plan to redesign the crossing of Nordelva from a culvert to a bridge solution and make other adjustments to reduce the number of needed dispensations to three. They express concern that the requested changes by the authorities may compromise the quality of the alpine solution. They request a meeting to further discuss the situation.The Troms\u00f8 municipality has received a decision regarding the detailed regulation for an alpine facility in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn. The plan has been approved by the Ministry of Local Government and Modernisation. The Sami Parliament has requested revisions to the plan to address concerns about cultural heritage sites and reindeer husbandry. The municipality is expected to make the necessary revisions.The email exchange involves discussions regarding a reissued building permit for Arctic Center. The sender, Thea Solvoll Liahjell, indicates that certain documentation requirements are not met and requests for them to be provided. The recipient, Erik Joachimsen, expresses urgency in obtaining the permit and asks for an update. Anders Koller Tufte provides updated plans and documents related to the project. There are also mentions of communication issues and requests for confirmation of receipt of emails.Troms\u00f8 Kommune, seksjon for byutvikling og byggesak, har mottatt en henvendelse ang\u00e5ende etableringen av skianlegget \"Arctic Center\". Kommunen har mottatt h\u00f8ringsdokumentet med frist til 19. april 2023, og det s\u00f8kes om oppf\u00f8ring av 7 tiltak, inkludert parkeringsanlegg, vei, velkomstsenter, skiheiser og terrenginngrep. Enhet for klima, milj\u00f8 og landbruk har kommentarer til flere av de dispensasjonss\u00f8kte tiltakene, blant annet kulvert for broer over Nordelva. Det s\u00f8kes om \u00e5 erstatte broer med en kulvert p\u00e5 35 meter lengde.\n\nElvedalen i Naturbase er beskrevet som en bj\u00f8rkeskog med h\u00f8gstauder, en artsrik og produktiv skogtype. En godkjent brol\u00f8sning vil ivareta landskapet og elvel\u00f8pet tilfredsstillende samtidig som elvedalen kan opprettholde sine funksjoner i naturen, til tross for n\u00e6rliggende aktivitet. Elvedalen fungerer som leveomr\u00e5de og korridor for arter som ferdes i omr\u00e5det, og inneholder blant annet en liten bestand av \u00f8rret. En planlagt kulvert vil v\u00e6re en stor barriere for \u00f8rreten og annet dyreliv, og vil fylle inn elvedalen i en bredde p\u00e5 minimum 35 m og en lengde estimert fra 30 til 60-70 m avhengig av fyllingens h\u00f8yde.\n\nDet s\u00f8kes om ulike endringer og dispensasjoner i forbindelse med etablering av Arctic Center. Disse endringene inkluderer en kulvert i stedet for broer over elven, flytting av topp- og bunnstasjon for stolheiser, etablering av en vannledning, terrenginngrep for velkomstsenter og parkeringsareal. Det trekkes frem bekymringer knyttet til konsekvensene for naturmangfoldet, spesielt i forhold til vannforekomster og partikkelavrenning til elver. Det ble anbefalt \u00e5 avsl\u00e5 dispensasjonene p\u00e5 grunn av den store p\u00e5virkningen p\u00e5 omr\u00e5dets landskap og dyreliv. Krisen Kloosterman og Bo Eide utarbeidet dokumentet.Anders Koller Tufte sent an email to various recipients regarding a building permit for the Arctic Center. He attached drawings of a bridge over the Nordelva river and requested a meeting to discuss new drawings and interpretations for the building permit process.The updated application with a new bridge structure has been sent on internal consultation to the municipality's unit for climate, environment, and agriculture. They believe that the bridge is a better environmental alternative than the originally proposed culvert. However, they have concerns about the significant impact on the river's course and the lack of detailed plans or actions to minimize environmental damage.\n\nKML mener at det m\u00e5 v\u00e6re p\u00e5 plass en konsekvensutredning og tilstrekkelig kunnskapsgrunnlag i henhold til forvaltningsloven og vannforskriften f\u00f8r kommunen kan behandle forslaget om ny aktivitet eller inngrep som p\u00e5virker Nordelva. Det er behov for kartlegging av \u00f8kologisk potensiale og kjemisk tilstand i elva, samt vurdering av tiltak for \u00e5 opprettholde milj\u00f8m\u00e5let. KML st\u00f8tter l\u00f8sningen med bru istedenfor kulvert, men krever mer detaljert beskrivelse og planer for \u00e5 hindre milj\u00f8konsekvensene ved endring av elvel\u00f8pet. Det m\u00e5 ogs\u00e5 gjennomf\u00f8res en grundig kartlegging av milj\u00f8tilstanden i Nordelva f\u00f8r tiltaket kan godkjennes.\n\nAgnete Pedersen Evertsen, klima- og milj\u00f8r\u00e5dgiver, kan kontaktes for sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l om uttalelsen og saksbehandlingen etter vannforskriften. En oppdatert s\u00f8knad med ny bru-konstruksjon er sendt p\u00e5 intern h\u00f8ring til kommunen, og enheten for klima, milj\u00f8 og landbruk mener at broen er et bedre milj\u00f8messig alternativ enn den opprinnelig foresl\u00e5tte kulverten. Endringen av elvel\u00f8pet anses som et betydelig naturinngrep, men innsendte dokumenter er ikke tilstrekkelige for \u00e5 avgj\u00f8re milj\u00f8konsekvensene. Planer og tiltak for \u00e5 hindre forringelse av naturen mangler.\n\nKML mener at det er viktig med tilstrekkelig kunnskapsgrunnlag f\u00f8r et forslag om ny aktivitet eller nye inngrep som p\u00e5virker en vannforekomst kan saksbehandles av kommunen. De peker p\u00e5 behovet for kartlegging av \u00f8kologisk potensiale og kjemisk tilstand i elva Nordelva f\u00f8r eventuelle tiltak kan settes i verk. KML st\u00f8tter bru-l\u00f8sningen fremfor kulvert, men krever ytterligere beskrivelser av tiltaket, kartlegging av milj\u00f8tilstanden og en plan for \u00e5 hindre milj\u00f8konsekvenser. De p\u00e5peker s\u00e6rlig behovet for kartlegging av milj\u00f8tilstanden i Nordelva f\u00f8r saken kan godkjennes.\n\nThea Solvoll Liahjell, jurist for Seksjon for Byutvikling og Byggesak i Troms\u00f8 kommune, can be contacted for questions regarding statements and processing under the Water Framework Directive. She provided information in an email regarding the need for additional documentation for a specific project, including details on access roads, flood protection requirements, and compliance with environmental laws. There was a request for clarification from a recipient regarding the specific requirements mentioned in the letter, indicating potential confusion on the part of the project applicants.Eirik Myhrvold is sending a complaint to the Troms\u00f8 municipality regarding a building permit application by Artic Center to change the sewage system to a filter system and lay cables in the area. He believes this change should not be approved as it could lead to contamination of nearby wetlands and rivers. He identifies himself as a neighbor in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn.In this email exchange, Anders Koller Tufte responds to Thea Solvoll Liahjell and Erik Joachimsen regarding a meeting held on June 28, 2023. He expresses concerns about the lack of references to topics discussed in the meeting, especially regarding the assessment of individual dispensations related to the construction of a ski center. He also raises concerns about the potential consequences of altering the course of the Nordelva river and the lack of involvement from the environmental department in the decision-making process. Tufte requests a more thorough understanding of the dispensations being requested and the overall impact of the construction project.Anders Koller Tufte, an architect at Ihuga AS, sent an email regarding a supplementary neighbor notification related to the Arctic Center development project. Eight comments were received, and the attachments include responses to the comments along with additional information submitted for the development application.Arbeidstilsynet har mottatt en s\u00f8knad om samtykke etter arbeidsmilj\u00f8loven for et skianlegg og idrettshall i Troms\u00f8. De har sendt flere purringer om manglende informasjon og ber om at s\u00f8knaden trekkes eller at informasjonen leveres innen fristen. Kommunen kan ikke gi tillatelse uten Arbeidstilsynets samtykke. Tiltakshaver m\u00e5 informere arbeidsmilj\u00f8utvalget, verneombudet eller ansattes representant. Mer informasjon om kravene og rettighetene finnes p\u00e5 Arbeidstilsynets nettside.Statsforvalteren melder om kontaktinformasjon og ulike adresser for henvendelser. De mottar en s\u00f8knad om dispensasjon for etablering av et alpinanlegg i Troms\u00f8 kommune, med en utsatt frist for h\u00f8ring til 24.05.23. Prosjektet inkluderer ulike tiltak som parkeringsanlegg, veier, velkomstsenter, skiheis, og andre anlegg. Det er ogs\u00e5 planlagt \u00e5 opparbeide gang- og sykkeladkomst fra en eksisterende vei.\n\nDet s\u00f8kes om 10 dispensasjoner knyttet til reguleringsplanene for omr\u00e5det hvor tiltakene \u00f8nskes plassert. Kommuneplanens arealdel og reguleringsplanene for omr\u00e5det m\u00e5 f\u00f8lges, men det kan gis dispensasjon dersom det er n\u00f8dvendig. Dispensasjonene s\u00f8kes blant annet for overskridelse av utnyttingsgrad i omr\u00e5det.\n\nThe document is a referral from Troms\u00f8 Municipality to the Statsforvalteren regarding a application for 12 exemptions for the establishment of the ski resort \"Arctic Center\" in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn on Kval\u00f8ya. The project includes various infrastructure developments such as parking facilities, roads, ski lifts, technical facilities, and water and sewage systems. The properties where the developments are proposed are covered by three different land use plans. The Statsforvalteren has been given an extended deadline for the consultation until May 24, 2023.\n\nRegularization plans will apply side by side, with plan 1875 taking precedence over plan 1515 in case of conflict, according to the Planning and Building Act \u00a7 1-5. There are requests for 10 exemptions related to regulation plan \"Arctic Center, H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn\" (plan-id 1515) and 2 exemptions for \"Detailed regulation for the ski resort in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn, lower part of Arctic Center\" (plan-id 1875). The exemptions include exceeding building utilization, placement of ski lifts, heistraseers, and culvert establishment in specified areas of the plans.\n\nDet s\u00f8kes om dispensasjoner knyttet til ulike omr\u00e5der og dokumentasjonskrav i reguleringsplanen. Statsforvalteren mener at det er grunnleggende mangler i det eksisterende plangrunnlaget og at det b\u00f8r gjennomf\u00f8res en planendring istedenfor enkeltst\u00e5ende dispensasjoner. Andre sektormyndigheter har ogs\u00e5 pekt p\u00e5 potensielle konflikter og behov for oppdatering av planen. Det understrekes at dispensasjon fra arealplaner reiser spesielle sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l og at planer b\u00f8r f\u00f8lges inntil de oppheves eller endres. Statsforvalteren ber om \u00e5 bli informert om kommunens avgj\u00f8relse og varsler mulig p\u00e5klaging av dispensasjoner.The Sami Parliament reminds that plans for a new water and sewage network outside the regulated area of the Arctic Center must be sent to them for review and feedback.Anne \u00d8vrejorde R\u00f8dven, an official from Troms fylkeskommune, sent an email to Thea Solvoll Liahjell and Maria Wilhelmsen from Troms\u00f8 kommune regarding the need for clarifications on a decision related to the establishment of a ski facility. They requested a meeting to discuss how their input on transportation concerns was considered in the decision. The email proposed several time slots for the meeting and asked for a prompt response. Anne \u00d8vrejorde R\u00f8dven also mentioned her new email address for future correspondence.Karianne Laagstein is inquiring about the status of a new regulatory plan after twelve applications for dispensation were submitted. Thea Solvoll Liahjell from Troms\u00f8 kommune responds, directing Karianne to the online portal for relevant documents and stating that they are currently processing the application but cannot provide a timeline for completion. Karianne requests a brief overview and timeline of the Arctic Center case from 2023-2024. Thea provides documents related to the new consultation for the Arctic Center ski facility and apologizes for any inconvenience.Supplementary application for Troms\u00f8 Resort, seeking dispensation from planning regulations and documentation requirements. The responsible applicant is IHUGA AS, and the project is being carried out by Arctic Center AS. Numerous attachments have been included with the application.Lone H\u00f8gda, a senior advisor at Statsforvalteren, requested an extension for a dispensation for the Arctic Center ski resort in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn on Kval\u00f8ya due to limited resources and high workload. They asked for a response by May 24, 2023, and requested a confirmation of the request for an extension from Troms\u00f8 kommune. The email was also copied to NVE.Bes\u00f8ksadresse, postadresse, kontaktinformasjon, og organisasjonsnummer for Troms\u00f8 kommune, informasjon om en bygges\u00f8knad for et alpinanlegg kalt \"Arctic Center\" med flere dispensasjoner, forel\u00f8pige vurderinger fra kommunen inkludert mulig avslag p\u00e5 noen dispensasjoner, frister for saksbehandling og konsultasjonsplikt med samiske interesser, samt krav om supplerende dokumentasjon og eventuelle endringer i s\u00f8knaden. Avsenderne av brevet er Anne-Marte T\u00f8gersen og Thea Solvoll Liahjell fra Seksjon for byutvikling, Byggesak i Troms\u00f8 kommune.This is a letter from Samediggi - Sametinget in response to a municipality's request for feedback on a building permit application. Sametinget maintains their initial statement opposing the application due to potential harm to a culturally protected site. They state that the application cannot be approved until certain conditions are met, including an archaeological survey of the site. They reference input from the Statsforvalteren in Troms and Finnmark regarding planning aspects. The letter is signed by senior advisors from Samediggi.Norges vassdrags- og energidirektorat (NVE) har uttalt seg i forbindelse med en s\u00f8knad om dispensasjon for et alpinanlegg i Troms\u00f8 kommune. NVE frar\u00e5der at tillatelse gis til tiltak som ber\u00f8rer vassdrag f\u00f8r en konsesjonspliktvurdering etter vannressursloven er gjennomf\u00f8rt. De mener kommunen ikke har vurdert dispensasjonen tilstrekkelig og at hensynet til vassdraget ikke er tilstrekkelig ivaretatt. NVE henviser til veiledning p\u00e5 deres nettsider for mer informasjon om hvordan hensynet til vassdraget kan ivaretas.Anders Koller Tufte is expressing concern about the extended deadline for responding to the neighbor notification regarding water and sewage plans in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn. Andrea Schneider acknowledges the concern but also notes that there are holiday days to consider in the timeline. She plans to submit a comment on the matter.\n\nA Project Coordinator from CIRFA at UiT The Arctic University of Norway in Troms\u00f8 is discussing plans for water and sewage lines in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn with other stakeholders. There is a request to extend the deadline for a response to a neighbor notification, as the current deadline of May 16th is considered too long. The coordinator will submit feedback, but reminds everyone that the departure is on the 19th.\n\nAndrea received information about a project with only 4 working days before the departure date, which she finds to be too short notice. She expresses concern about potential impacts on the surrounding environment and natural resources, but is reassured by the sender that measures will be taken to protect them during the project.\n\nAndrea Schneider har ikke mottatt nabovarsel ang\u00e5ende planene for en vann- og kloakkledning i H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn ved Troms\u00f8, til tross for at naboer i omr\u00e5det har f\u00e5tt informasjon. Hun ber om en forklaring p\u00e5 dette og \u00f8nsker \u00e5 utsette svarfristen da hun skal v\u00e6re p\u00e5 forskningstokt uten mobil- og internettdekning. Anders Koller Tufte forst\u00e5r hennes bekymringer og gir henne en utsatt frist for \u00e5 gi inn merknader, samtidig som han p\u00e5peker fordelene ved den nye VA-l\u00f8sningen. Han opplyser at dokumenter er tilgjengelige og at tekniske sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l kan rettes til prosjekterende for VA-l\u00f8sningen.Anders Koller Tufte is requesting the Troms\u00f8 municipality to contact relevant parties for a consultation regarding the building permit for the Arctic Center, as requested by the Sami Parliament.Anders Koller Tufte is concerned about a misinterpretation in the communication regarding the location of a water pipeline in relation to a cultural heritage site. He emphasizes that there is no need for excavation within the heritage site and urges for clarity in the wording of the communication to avoid negativity. Thea Solvoll Liahjell clarifies the division of authority between the municipality and the Sami Parliament, emphasizing that decisions related to cultural heritage should be discussed with the relevant authorities.The email exchange discusses the requirements for the development of the Arctic Center, specifically relating to forestry, agriculture, and reindeer management plans. The responsibility falls under the KML department, and plans need to be approved before construction can begin. There is a request for a meeting to clarify the specific requirements for the plan, including a forestry plan that has been pending approval since 2012. The email also mentions the need for an updated reindeer management plan and a discussion on the expectations for these plans to streamline the approval process.Eirik Myhrvold, an agronom, is submitting a complaint against the Artic Center for seeking a change in the water and sewage system and requesting a dispensation from a regulation plan. He argues that due to the wetland and stream system in the area, there are significant environmental risks that could negatively impact a nearby wetland area crucial for bird life. He believes the disadvantages outweigh the advantages and strongly opposes the project.IHUGA AS, located in Oslo, has been granted permission to establish a ski resort in Troms\u00f8. The responsible applicant is IHUGA AS, and the project owner is ARCTIC CENTER AS. The building department has granted approval for the ski resort as applied for, with some exceptions under the planning and building laws. The permission includes dispensation for the placement of ski lifts and other structures, as well as the installation of underground water pipelines.\n\nTiltaksklasser fastsettes etter s\u00f8kers forslag i gjennomf\u00f8ringsplanen, som m\u00e5 oppdateres med gjeldende ansvarsretter. Uavhengig kontroll m\u00e5 gjennomf\u00f8res for bygningsfysikk, konstruksjonssikkerhet, geoteknikk og brannsikringskonsept. Tiltaket kan ikke startes f\u00f8r igangsettingstillatelse er gitt og dokumentasjon som tekniske detaljplaner for offentlig trafikk og gr\u00f8ntareal er vedlagt s\u00f8knaden. Dokumentasjon og godkjente detaljplaner for kryssl\u00f8sninger og avkj\u00f8rsler til eiendommene m\u00e5 ogs\u00e5 v\u00e6re p\u00e5 plass.\n\nStatens Vegvesen er godkjenningsmyndighet for tiltak i planomr\u00e5det. F\u00f8r igangsettingstillatelse kan gis, m\u00e5 skogbruksplan og beitebruksplan godkjennes av landbruksmyndigheten i kommunen. Det m\u00e5 ogs\u00e5 foreligge en forvaltningsplan for reindriften i omr\u00e5det. Videre m\u00e5 offentlig samferdselsanlegg v\u00e6re opparbeidet, og avkj\u00f8rsel til flere eiendommer m\u00e5 v\u00e6re p\u00e5 plass f\u00f8r tillatelse gis til bygninger og anlegg i planomr\u00e5det.\n\nSummary: The development of the driveway must comply with the guidelines of the Norwegian Public Roads Administration. Before permits can be issued for buildings and facilities in the area, noise barriers must be set up. Permits for specific projects within designated areas cannot be given until sewage treatment facilities are in place. Temporary permits cannot be issued until all requirements are met and the areas designated for public use are approved by the municipality. Consent from the Labour Inspection Authority is required, and the implementation plan must be updated with responsible entities. The decision can be appealed within three weeks to the State Administration in Troms and Finnmark. More information can be found in the provided documents.\n\nDette er et dokument fra Seksjon for byutvikling, byggesak signert av Maria Wilhelmsen og Thea Solvoll Liahjell. Dokumentet er elektronisk godkjent og har ingen signatur. Det inneholder nyttige opplysninger hvis man \u00f8nsker \u00e5 klage p\u00e5 vedtak, samt en rekke vedlegg som blant annet gjennomf\u00f8ringsplan, avkj\u00f8rselsplan, fasadetegninger og ulike plantegninger.\n\nThis document includes various plans and drawings related to a sewage system, welcome center, ski lifts, and other infrastructure. It also lists recipients who need to be informed of the project, such as government authorities, legal firms, and individuals involved in the project. The document also outlines the process of handling the application for a building permit, including the dates of receiving and sending documents, as well as the need for additional information.\n\nA request for additional information was made on 08.03.2023, followed by responses from various entities such as the Sami Parliament, local authorities, and the Norwegian Water Resources and Energy Directorate. The application was updated on 12.06.2023, and a consultation offer was made under the Sami Act on 19.06.2023. Additional documentation was submitted on 11.07.2023 and 31.08.2023, leading to the submission of a complete emission permit application on 24.09.2023. A new request for feedback was issued on 20.12.2023, and a warning for a fee due to delays was given on 09.01.2024. Further feedback from the Norwegian Water Resources and Energy Directorate and the Sami Parliament was requested on 19.01.2024 and 30.01.2024, respectively. The current plans for the property include various zoning regulations dating back to 1988, with the proposed development including parking facilities, roads, a welcome center, and ski lifts.\n\nSummary: The project includes the establishment of parking facilities, ski lifts (Bytrekket, Tilbringerheisen, Crosstrekket, Stolheis 1, and Stolheis 2), associated slopes and lift houses for T2, T3, and T5, terrain modifications in areas 1, 2, and 3, and the establishment of a water and sewage solution. Specific details include the establishment of parking facilities and a traffic square, construction of roads and technical facilities including access roads and a bridge over Nordelva, and the placement of a welcome center at the bottom of the ski resort.\n\nThe document provides information about the size of the land, the built area, the degree of exploitation, and the roof heights for a ski resort development. It seeks permission to build six ski lifts with associated runs and lift houses. The lifts include a magic carpet, T-bar, and chairlifts, with integrated lift houses at the top and bottom stations. There are also requests for terrain alterations in three areas, including the construction of a bridge and other changes near the bottom station of one of the chairlifts.\n\nSummary: The project includes terrain modifications around the welcome center, ski square, and delivery area to accommodate the construction of these facilities in steep terrain with significant height differences. Additionally, there is a proposal to lay water supply pipelines in an area designated for agriculture, nature, outdoor activities, and reindeer husbandry. Risk analyses have been conducted for floods and landslides, with further detailed assessments and possible mitigation measures to be undertaken in later stages. The water and sewage solutions are in accordance with regulations, with approval from relevant authorities.\n\nThe Municipality's water and sewage department has issued a discharge permit on December 20, 2023. The case has been on public consultation twice. In the first consultation round, concerns were raised about the risk of damage to a protected cultural monument due to the placement of a water pipeline, and the need for a separate permit for such intervention. The Department also addressed the potential increase in traffic towards a summer residence area due to the establishment of a ski lift, but believed that with proper guidance and monitoring, the risks could be managed.\n\nSametinget viser til bestemmelser i planen som begrenser terrenginngrepene under skitrekket til et minimum. Departementet understreket at driftsveien m\u00e5 opparbeides sk\u00e5nsomt for tilsyn og vedlikehold, og at anleggsomr\u00e5det m\u00e5 plasseres for \u00e5 minimere skade. Sametinget p\u00e5pekte at planen kan v\u00e6re i konflikt med reindriftsloven, og at kommunen m\u00e5 konsultere ber\u00f8rte samiske interesser. Troms og Finnmark fylkeskommune anbefaler ikke \u00e5 behandle saken som en dispensasjonssak p\u00e5 grunn av manglende utredning rundt trafikksikkerhet og andre uavklarte punkter. Disse inkluderer uklarheter om \u00f8kning i trafikkmengde og potensiell negativ virkning for trafikksikkerheten i omr\u00e5det.\n\nUtryknings- og motoriserte kj\u00f8ret\u00f8y i alpintraseen kan p\u00e5virkes av tiltakene, det vil v\u00e6re krav om s\u00f8knad for endring av avkj\u00f8rsel for gang- og sykkeladkomst. Anleggsveien er et uavklart punkt i s\u00f8knaden med tanke p\u00e5 plassering og krav til tilbakef\u00f8ring. Flomfaren er ogs\u00e5 et bekymringspunkt siden elva skal legges om p\u00e5 et lite strekk, og kulverl\u00f8sningen er ikke dimensjonert for en 100-\u00e5rs hendelse. Kommunen har plikt til \u00e5 vurdere om den gjeldende detaljreguleringen fortsatt er et aktuelt grunnlag for ny utbygging.\n\nKommunen skal vurdere s\u00f8knader om utbygging i omr\u00e5der med planer, med fokus p\u00e5 offentlige og private interesser, lokale forhold, arealpolitikk og planfaglig kvalitet. NVE og Statsforvalteren har uttrykt bekymring og motstand mot tiltak som ber\u00f8rer vassdrag uten tilstrekkelig vurdering av konsekvenser. Statsforvalteren mener det er behov for en helhetlig planavklaring i stedet for enkeltst\u00e5ende dispensasjoner. Etter endringer i s\u00f8knaden ble den sendt p\u00e5 ny h\u00f8ring for ytterligere vurdering.\n\nEndringer i tiltaket har gjort det mer i tr\u00e5d med gjeldende arealplaner. Et nytt h\u00f8ringsbrev viser at endringen av s\u00f8knaden reduserer sannsynligheten for konflikt med et samisk kulturminne. NVE har ingen ytterligere merknader s\u00e5 lenge byggeplanene ikke p\u00e5virker vassdragets verdi og flom- og skredrisiko tas hensyn til ved kryssing av vassdrag. Troms fylkeskommune peker p\u00e5 nasjonale bestemmelser mot nedbygging av myr og oppfordrer til \u00e5 vurdere hensynet til myr n\u00f8ye. En planlagt gang- og sykkelvei avviker fra reguleringsplanen, if\u00f8lge fylkeskommunen.\n\nFylkeskommunen krever dispensasjon fra LNFR-form\u00e5let og at kollektivanlegg m\u00e5 opparbeides i henhold til statens vegvesens h\u00e5ndb\u00f8ker. De frar\u00e5der kommunen \u00e5 gi dispensasjon p\u00e5 grunn av hensyn til kollektivtransporten, trafikksikkerhet og trafikkavvikling. Kommunen har endret s\u00f8knaden basert p\u00e5 sektormyndighetenes innspill. Det er mottatt merknader ang\u00e5ende nedbygging av myr og gang- og sykkelvei i andre h\u00f8ringsrunde. Kommunen viser til reguleringsplanbestemmelsene for \u00e5 sikre at tiltak innenfor faresonen utf\u00f8res i samsvar med kravene.\n\nKommunen informerer om at plan- og bygningsloven gir tiltakshaver rett til tillatelse for tiltak som er i tr\u00e5d med gjeldende lover og arealplaner for eiendommen. Eventuelle senere tiltak m\u00e5 s\u00f8kes som en egen byggesak. Kommunen mener at reguleringsplanene for omr\u00e5det er oppdaterte, og tiltakene er i tr\u00e5d med planen. Eventuelle dispensasjoner vil ikke ha negativ innvirkning p\u00e5 trafikk eller samferdsel. Reguleringsplanen angir hvilken dokumentasjon som kreves for \u00e5 f\u00e5 igangsettingstillatelse.\n\nThe order requirements in the plan state that the Norwegian Public Roads Administration must approve detailed plans for the intersection between SKV1, SKV2, and the driveway to properties 66/46, 66/78, 66/108, 66/109, 66/121, 66/65, and 66/40 before the municipality can issue a building permit. Consultation was offered to the affected reindeer herding district as per the Sami Act Chapter 4, but no response was received. Neighbors have been notified of the project, and the municipality has received feedback from several neighbors listed by their property numbers and names.\n\nSiljan Mari Viken, Henriette Sofie Pettersen, Eirik Aronsen, og Ane Elene Johansen har alle sendt inn merknader ang\u00e5ende planer om en VAO-l\u00f8sning som involverer vann- og avl\u00f8psledninger tilknyttet Eidkjosen. Bekymringer inkluderer at vannledningen ligger utenfor reguleringsplanens grenser, fare for forurensning av private br\u00f8nner og kvikkleireskred, samt generell kritikk av skianlegget og s\u00f8knader om dispensasjoner grunnet omr\u00e5dets naturreservatstatus. Nabomerknaden fra Ane Elene Johansen ble diskutert, men ble bemerket at leietakere ikke regnes som naboer i plan- og bygningsloven.\n\nDet anbefales at det ikke gis dispensasjon fra testing av vann p\u00e5 grunn av bekymringer rundt grunnvannsniv\u00e5, lekkasje fra myr og anlegg til Nordelva, og risiko for forurensning av fosfor og andre n\u00e6ringsstoffer i et s\u00e5rbart omr\u00e5de. Naboenes merknader inkluderer bekymringer rundt manglende informasjon og \u00f8nsker om st\u00f8yskjerm, trygg skolevei, og motstand mot bygging av sykkell\u00f8ype i et omr\u00e5de som skal v\u00e6re stengt til bondens behov. s\u00f8keren har f\u00e5tt beskjed om disse merknadene.\n\nIn 2022, it was initially planned to connect a water and sewage pipeline to Eidkjosen via sea lines. However, due to numerous negative feedback, the plan was changed back to the original VAO solution approved with the zoning plan. This change involved establishing a private water supply system with corresponding water pipelines and a private sewage system within the planned area. Approval was granted by the Food Safety Authority on 01.11.2022, and the municipality's Water and Sewer Department has issued a discharge permit. The construction will take place near a nature reserve with abundant bird life, but measures will be taken to minimize disturbances, such as avoiding construction during the bird nesting season. The impact on bird life during the construction phase is expected to be short-lived, and little evidence of the construction work will remain once the facility is operational. The construction work will also consider and adapt to the activities in the reserve. Additionally, noise barriers are required for a specific property in zoning plan 1875.\n\nDet gis tillatelse til \u00e5 starte oppf\u00f8ring av bygninger og anlegg innenfor planomr\u00e5det etter en vurdering av hvilke eiendommer som ville bli negativt ber\u00f8rt. Tiltaket skal f\u00f8res opp i tr\u00e5d med reguleringsplanen, og det er gjort vurderinger ang\u00e5ende trafikksikkerhet og vei. Nabovarselet har v\u00e6rt omfattende p\u00e5 grunn av behovet knyttet til etableringen av Arctic Center, men hensikten har v\u00e6rt \u00e5 sikre at naboer f\u00e5r all n\u00f8dvendig informasjon om planlagte tiltak. Plan- og bygningsloven gir tiltakshaver rett p\u00e5 \u00e5 f\u00e5 tillatelse til oppf\u00f8ring av tiltak i tr\u00e5d med gjeldende bestemmelser, og skianlegget oppf\u00f8res i hovedsak i tr\u00e5d med reguleringsplanene for omr\u00e5det, med unntak av noen dispensasjoner.\n\nNaboene er bekymret for endringer i skianlegget og vannledningen i sitt omr\u00e5de, men kommunen har godkjent tiltakene etter grundige planprosesser. Selv om det var mange dispensasjoner og dokumenter involvert, har flere blitt trukket tilbake. Naboene er spesielt bekymret for tiltak p\u00e5 deres eiendommer uten tilstrekkelig avklaring p\u00e5 forh\u00e5nd, spesielt med hensyn til vannledningen som n\u00e5 er fjernet.\n\nBygningsmyndighetene har begrenset mulighet til \u00e5 blande seg inn i privatrettslige sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l i behandlingen av bygges\u00f8knader. If\u00f8lge Plan- og bygningsloven kan s\u00f8knader avvises hvis det er \u00e5penbart at tiltakshaver ikke har de n\u00f8dvendige privatrettslige rettighetene. I denne saken har kommunen funnet at s\u00f8keren oppfyller kravene, og det er ikke kommet inn merknader fra naboer som tilsier at s\u00f8knaden ikke kan godkjennes. I tillegg m\u00e5 ethvert tiltak ha gode visuelle kvaliteter i forhold til funksjon, omgivelser og plassering i henhold til Plan- og bygningsloven.\n\nKommunen kan vurdere hensynet til historiske, arkitektoniske og kulturelle verdier ved tiltak knyttet til et eksisterende byggverks ytre. Den oms\u00f8kte skianlegget oppfyller kravene til visuelle kvaliteter og er tilpasset sitt naturlige milj\u00f8. Naturmangfoldet i omr\u00e5det er utredet, og det er identifisert verneverdier langs Nordelva. Risiko- og s\u00e5rbarhetsanalyse har avdekket viktige omr\u00e5der som m\u00e5 tas hensyn til. Planomr\u00e5det ber\u00f8rer ogs\u00e5 et omr\u00e5de med naturtype gr\u00e5or/heggeskog vurdert til A verdi.\n\nPlanned measures will not result in the seizure of these natural types, as the activity of the ski area is associated with the winter season and the activity around the ravine area is limited, it will be possible to delimit and minimize interventions along the Nordelva. According to our assessment, the knowledge base is sufficient to evaluate the location of the measure.\n\nThe precautionary principle is applied when there is not enough knowledge to know the effects the decision will have on biodiversity. If there is a risk of serious or irreversible damage to biodiversity, lack of knowledge should not be used as a reason to delay or refrain from taking management measures.\n\nBased on the knowledge base we have, we do not see that the proposed measure will lead to significant adverse consequences for the landscape, ecosystem, natural types, and species in the area, beyond what has already been considered in previous planning processes.\n\nThe overall burden on an ecosystem is assessed in section 10 of the Nature Diversity Act. To assess the consequences of the measure on the natural environment, the measure is therefore considered in conjunction with other completed or planned measures in the area. The establishment of a ski resort as applied for will, in the municipality's assessment, to a small extent lead to a burden on the ecosystem beyond what has already been considered in previous planning processes.\n\nIn the 1875 regulatory plan from 2020, it is considered that commercial activities will be allowed within certain areas, potentially causing increased impact on the area beyond what currently exists. However, this impact has been deemed acceptable through the planning process. For developments not covered by the plan, specific regulations must be met to address potential environmental impacts. The costs of environmental degradation must be covered by the developer, unless it is deemed unreasonable based on the nature of the project and the damage caused. The ski resort construction will follow the existing regulatory plan with a few exceptions, which have been approved based on minimal additional impact on biodiversity. Overall, the ski resort development has taken into account environmental considerations and has been deemed permissible by the municipality.\n\nFor at tiltaket skal v\u00e6re mest mulig sk\u00e5nsomt for milj\u00f8et og naturmangfoldet i omr\u00e5det, m\u00e5 det tas i bruk milj\u00f8forsvarlige teknikker og driftsmetoder. Dette inneb\u00e6rer \u00e5 velge driftsmetoder, tekniske l\u00f8sninger og lokalisering som tar hensyn til milj\u00f8et, samfunnet og \u00f8konomien. Kommunen forventer at gjennomf\u00f8ringen av tiltaket skjer p\u00e5 en sk\u00e5nsom m\u00e5te for naturmilj\u00f8et. Dispensasjoner er s\u00f8kt for \u00e5 kunne plassere heistraseer og stolheiser i strid med gjeldende arealplaner, og disse behandlet punktvis.\n\nThe text discusses excerpts from a regulation plan regarding the placement of ski lift tracks T1, T2, T3, and T5, both upper and lower parts. It also mentions the basis for requesting a dispensation from the regulations. The applicant argues that minor adjustments are necessary to optimize the ski resort's layout, area use, and the effectiveness of lifts and slopes.\n\nMindre justeringer i plasseringen av heistraseene innenfor samme form\u00e5lsomr\u00e5de gj\u00f8res for \u00e5 optimalisere og forbedre arealbruk og funksjonen til reguleringen. Endringene vil ikke ha negative effekter, og fordelene med dispensasjonen vil v\u00e6re st\u00f8rre enn eventuelle ulemper. Hensynene bak bestemmelsen om plassering av heistraseene blir ikke vesentlig tilsidesatt, da m\u00e5let er \u00e5 sikre hensiktsmessig plassering innenfor skiomr\u00e5det og unng\u00e5 store terrenginngrep.\n\nThe application requests a relatively minor deviation from the allowed placements, which the municipality believes will not result in significant terrain disruption or move ski traffic outside the intended purpose. The municipality also notes that the new placements will optimize the ski facility and improve skier movement through the area, with minimal disadvantages. Consequently, the municipality believes that the benefits of granting the dispensation outweigh the drawbacks.\n\nGenerell ulempe ved \u00e5 gi dispensasjon er at det kan undergrave planer, men i dette tilfellet vil justerte plasseringer av heistraseene fortsatt ligge innenfor samme arealform\u00e5l og i samme retning som reguleringsplanen. Etter kommunens vurdering er fordelene ved dispensasjonen st\u00f8rre enn ulempene, og derfor har de besluttet \u00e5 gi dispensasjon. Dette er for \u00e5 sikre en viss grad av fleksibilitet og tillate en begrenset fravikelse av planen. Derfor blir dispensasjonen gitt for plasseringen av stolheis 1 og 2.\n\nDet s\u00f8kes om dispensasjon for \u00e5 forlenge Stolheis 1, redusere lengden p\u00e5 Stolheis 2 og plassere bunnstasjonen for Stolheis 2 n\u00e6rmere toppstasjonen til Stolheis 1 enn det som er planlagt. Dette vil bidra til bedre skiforhold p\u00e5 vindfulle dager. Dispensasjon kan gis dersom fordelene er st\u00f8rre enn ulempene, og kommunen har mulighet, men ikke plikt til \u00e5 gi dispensasjon.\n\nIn the current plan 1515, the top \"Chairlift 1\" and bottom \"Chairlift 2\" are placed with a relatively large distance between them. It is desired to have greater proximity between these two points for the sake of operation, experience, infrastructure establishment, impact on nature, and commercial opportunities. The dispensation will allow for greater flexibility to achieve these effects. The dispensation will involve the establishment of the top station \"Chairlift 1\" within the area designated for the ski resort/alpine area, and parts of the bottom station for \"Chairlift 2\" will be established in the area designated for the ski resort/alpine area. The overall amount of lift infrastructure such as towers and top/bottom stations will remain unchanged. It will, however, facilitate more efficient use of established structures and functions, as well as increase the opportunities for joint use of areas related to the two stations. \n\nThe adjustment will have minimal negative effects. The visual experience of the mountain may be somewhat affected, but the landscape and situation after the change are relatively similar, and the increased distance will compensate somewhat for the area being moved \"higher in the mountain\". The benefits will include better operation and experience for guests, improved possibilities for establishing commercial offers and service functions, reduced impact on nature, and better options for skiers on windy days.\n\nDet er bedre forutsigbarhet for opplevelse og tilbud for brukere og operat\u00f8r n\u00e5r det gjelder skitrekkenes og skianleggenes plassering. Dispensasjon for endret plassering av skitrekkene anses som fordelaktige, da det vil f\u00f8re til f\u00e6rre terrenginngrep og en mer hensiktsmessig l\u00f8sning for skianlegget. Kommunen vurderer at bestemmelsen bak reguleringsplanen ikke blir vesentlig tilsidesatt ved \u00e5 gi dispensasjon, da avvikene er begrensede og ikke vil ha negativ virkning p\u00e5 arealet som benyttes som beiteomr\u00e5de p\u00e5 sommerstid.\n\nThe municipality has determined that the proposed ski lift relocation will not significantly disregard the considerations behind the regulation or the purpose of the law, meeting the first condition for granting a dispensation. The second condition, that the benefits of granting the dispensation must clearly outweigh the drawbacks, is also met in this case. The new locations for ski lifts 1 and 2 offer significant advantages, such as reducing environmental impact, improving skiers' movement through the facility, and better suitability for weather conditions. The municipality does not see many disadvantages to granting the dispensation in this instance, as the benefits outweigh any potential drawbacks. It is noted that granting dispensations may generally undermine planning and decision-making processes.\n\nKommunen vurderer at dispensasjon kan gis for justert plassering av skitrekkene Stolheis 1 og 2 p\u00e5 grunn av begrensede endringer i planen og de fordelene det gir med f\u00e6rre inngrep i naturen og bedre egnet plassering. Kommunen konkluderer med \u00e5 gi dispensasjon for dette tiltaket.\n\nKommunen har mulighet til \u00e5 gi dispensasjon fra bestemmelser fastsatt etter plan- og bygningsloven hvis visse vilk\u00e5r er oppfylt. Dispensasjon kan ikke gis dersom hensynene bak bestemmelsen det dispenseres fra blir vesentlig tilsidesatt, og fordelene ved \u00e5 gi dispensasjon m\u00e5 v\u00e6re klart st\u00f8rre enn ulempene. Selv om kommunen har mulighet til \u00e5 gi dispensasjon, har ingen krav p\u00e5 det. En s\u00f8ker \u00f8nsker \u00e5 forlenge en stolheis og redusere lengden p\u00e5 en annen stolheis, samt plassere bunnstasjonen n\u00e6rmere toppstasjonen enn planen legger til rette for. Dette begrunnes med behov for bedre skiforhold p\u00e5 vindutsatte dager og forbedret drift og opplevelse.\n\nThe dispensation will allow for greater flexibility to achieve certain effects. It will involve the establishment of a top station \"Chairlift 1\" within the designated ski area/alpine area, as well as parts of the bottom station for \"Chairlift 2\" being established in the same area. The total amount of lift infrastructure will remain unchanged, but will facilitate more efficient use of established structures and increase opportunities for shared use of areas related to the two stations. \n\nThe adjustment will have minimal negative effects, with some potential impact on the visual experience of the mountain, but the landscape and situation remain relatively similar. The benefits include improved operation, flow, and connectivity between the two points for guests, as well as better opportunities for commercial offerings and services. There will be reduced impact on nature, improved options for skiers on windy days, and increased predictability for users and operators with less risk of wind affecting services. The benefits of granting the dispensation are therefore considered to outweigh the disadvantages.\n\nThe consideration behind the provision is not significantly disregarded. The purpose of the \"recreational area\" in regulation plan 1515 is to preserve the area as a natural area for skiing, outdoor activities, reindeer husbandry, and traditional agriculture. The recreational area is specified on the map where ski lifts and facilities can be built. The municipality believes that the purpose of the area will not be significantly disregarded by granting dispensation for the relocation of Ski Lifts 1 and 2, as the deviations from the plan are limited and the ski lifts will still be located near regulated ski facilities. The new locations are seen as more efficient for the ski resort with less terrain disturbance. The municipality does not believe that the new locations will greatly hinder the use of the area as intended. The municipality believes that the benefits of granting dispensation for the new ski lift locations outweigh the drawbacks, meeting the second requirement for dispensation.\n\nThe current plan for the ski lift stations allows for a significant distance between the top station for \"Lift 1\" and the bottom station for \"Lift 2\", but changes are being considered to place them closer together. This new arrangement would involve fewer disruptions to the natural environment and improve the flow of skiers through the resort. The municipality sees few drawbacks to granting an exception in this case, as the benefits of the adjustment outweigh any potential disadvantages. The municipality believes that the advantages of the exception are much greater than the disadvantages, and therefore the second condition for the exception is satisfied.\n\nKommunen kan gi dispensasjon etter skj\u00f8nn om vilk\u00e5rene er oppfylt, selv om det er begrenset avvik fra planen. I dette tilfellet \u00f8nskes dispensasjon for etablering av en nedgravd vannledning p\u00e5 et omr\u00e5de regulert til LNFR-areal. Kommunen vurderer at fordelene ved dispensasjonen er st\u00f8rre enn ulempene, og gir derfor dispensasjon.\n\nKommunen gir dispensasjon for et vannledningsprosjekt til et skianlegg, da fordelene vurderes \u00e5 v\u00e6re st\u00f8rre enn ulempene. Dispensasjonen anses \u00e5 ikke tilsidesette hensynet bak bestemmelsen om LNFR-omr\u00e5det. Flere dispensasjoner i samme byggesak vurderes ogs\u00e5 og godkjennes. Viktige opplysninger om forurensning, ansvar for igangsetting av tiltak, ferdigattest, tilsyn og gebyrer oppgis. Byggesaksgebyr p\u00e5 kr 183 600 faktureres til tiltakshaver.The email contains a h\u00f8ringsuttalelse (consultation response) from Troms County Council regarding an adjusted application. The sender, Thea Solvoll Liahjell, informs the recipients that the response has been registered and will be added to the postlist shortly. They mention that the recipients were not copied on the original email and offer to send the response if they wish to comment on it. The email is signed off with contact information for Thea Solvoll Liahjell, a lawyer in the Urban Development and Building section of the municipality.Anders Koller Tufte sent an email with an approved discharge permit for Arctic Center's planning application, as well as a separate email sending Christmas greetings.The email is from Anders Koller Tufte, a professional leader at ihuga.no, with the subject \"AC\" and an attachment related to a planning application for Troms\u00f8 resort phase 1. The email is addressed to Thea Solvoll Liahjell and postmottak@pbe.oslo.kommune.no. It also includes contact information for Anders Koller Tufte and links to the company website and social media accounts.The address for communication is R\u00e5dhusgata 2, 9008 Troms\u00f8, with a post address of Postboks 6900 Langnes, 9299 Troms\u00f8. The phone number is 77 79 00 00 and the email is postmottak@tromso.kommune.no. There is a request for comments on the establishment of the ski resort \"Arctic Center\" by IHUGA AS and ARCTIC CENTER AS. The application includes multiple planned measures and 12 exemptions from current land use plans. The application details the planning situation, measures, and exemptions in various points and attachments. The properties affected are covered by three land use plans.\n\nI henhold til kommuneplanens arealdel, skal gjeldende reguleringsplan gjelde uendret i omr\u00e5det. Det s\u00f8kes om oppf\u00f8ring og etablering av ulike tiltak, inkludert et parkeringsanlegg, veier, velkomstsenter, toppkaf\u00e9, skiheiser og terrenginngrep. Det vil ogs\u00e5 v\u00e6re n\u00f8dvendig med anleggsvei i forbindelse med skiheisene og infrastrukturen. Detaljert informasjon om tiltakene finnes i vedleggene til s\u00f8knaden.\n\nS\u00f8knad om etablering av veier og parkeringsomr\u00e5det, snuplass/vendehammer og gang- og sykkeltrase i et reguleringsomr\u00e5de. I tillegg s\u00f8kes det om \u00e5 etablere kulverter over Nordelva og langrennsl\u00f8ypen, samt plassering av et velkomstsenter og toppkaf\u00e9 i angitte omr\u00e5der i planene. Dispensasjoner er ogs\u00e5 nevnt i forbindelse med disse tiltakene.\u0449\n\nThis text refers to several attachments that provide details on the location and design of ski lifts and associated structures as part of a development project. The application includes six ski lifts with different types, and requests for permission for the construction of lift houses. The lifts are located within two different planning areas. Dispensations have been sought for the ski lifts and related facilities, with specific reference to dispensations for \"area 3\". Additional attachments provide situation maps and drawings of the lifts and facilities.\n\nS\u00f8knaden omfatter seks st\u00f8rre terrenginngrep som s\u00f8ker tillatelse til ulike endringer innenfor tre omr\u00e5der: etablering av en kulvert ved krysningen av Nordelva, terrenginngrep ved velkomstsenteret og vareleveringsomr\u00e5det, samt terrenginngrep for parkeringsomr\u00e5det. Det s\u00f8kes ogs\u00e5 om \u00e5 legge vannledning for vannforsyning til Arctic Center i et omr\u00e5de regulert til landbruk, natur, friluft og reindrift. Totalt s\u00f8kes det om 12 dispensasjoner, hvorav noen knytter seg til spesifikke omr\u00e5der og planer. Dispensasjoner s\u00f8kes ogs\u00e5 fra en bestemt del av en plan.\n\nDispensations granted for exceeding utilization rate in areas 2, 3, and 4, including placement of ski lifts, heistraseer, culverts, and snow depositories. Additionally, dispensations were granted for documentation requirements in the regulatory plan.\n\nThe document outlines various areas where dispensations are being sought for the development of a ski resort, including deviations from allowed land use and construction regulations. These include requests for exceeding building footprint limits, placement of ski lift stations in prohibited areas, and construction of culverts over a river. The document also lists relevant attachments, such as site maps and architectural plans. The municipality has requested input from various authorities and stakeholders within a specified timeframe.Troms and Finnmark County Council provides feedback on a request for dispensation for the establishment of the \"Arctic Center\" ski resort in Troms\u00f8. The application involves various planned actions, including parking facilities, roads, ski lifts, and infrastructure. The County Council highlights concerns regarding traffic, cultural heritage, and the need for further clarification on certain aspects of the project. They recommend that the application is not approved in its current form.Arctic Center planlegger endringer i sitt byggeprosjekt og har hatt et m\u00f8te med kommunen ang\u00e5ende dispensasjoner. Kommunen informerer om at antallet dispensasjoner og omfanget av endringene m\u00e5 vurderes n\u00f8ye. Arctic Center planlegger \u00e5 trekke flere dispensasjoner for \u00e5 im\u00f8tekomme kommunens anbefalinger. Kommunen informerer om kravene til vannledning og behovet for tillatelse fra Sametinget, samt endringen fra kulvert til bru og n\u00f8dvendigheten av dokumentasjon. Videre m\u00e5 s\u00f8keren sende inn dokumentasjon knyttet til endringene i prosjektet for \u00e5 kunne behandle s\u00f8knaden videre.This document outlines the landscape and vegetation plan for the Arctic Center project, including details on retaining existing terrain and vegetation, planting native species, and utilizing topsoil for re-vegetation. Further work will involve developing a detailed planting plan, addressing drainage and terrain shaping, and creating an restoration plan. The document also mentions the involvement of the landscape architects (LARK) in detailing the implementation of landscape and vegetation measures.Anders Koller Tufte is sending updated plans for the Arctic Center in a revised application to the Troms\u00f8 municipality. He attached several revised situation plans to ensure that all necessary documents are included.The email exchange is regarding a revised permit application for the Arctic Center. The sender indicates that the application is incomplete until documentation regarding compliance with the requirements of the zoning plan is received. They urge the recipients to send in the necessary documentation. There is also mention of urgency in obtaining the permit.Andrea Schneider is requesting an explanation for not receiving a neighbor notification and asks for an extension of the deadline due to being on a research expedition in weeks 16-19. She expresses the need for information about water and sewage pipeline plans in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn at Troms\u00f8. The email chain includes communication with Anders Koller Tufte and provides links to relevant documents for the project.Troms\u00f8 kommune har mottatt en s\u00f8knad om etablering av skianlegget \"Arctic Center\" p\u00e5 Kval\u00f8ya. De \u00f8nsker \u00e5 ha konsultasjon etter Sameloven kapittel 4 da tiltakene kan ber\u00f8re samiske interesser direkte. Kommunen har allerede informert reinbeitedistriktet, Sametinget, Statsforvalteren i Troms og Finnmark og Fylkeskommunen i Troms og Finnmark om saken. Det er ogs\u00e5 registrert kulturminner i omr\u00e5det som m\u00e5 tas hensyn til. De ber om tilbakemelding p\u00e5 \u00f8nske om konsultasjon innen fire uker.Anders Koller Tufte sent a follow-up email to Thea Solvoll Liahjell regarding the Arctic Center revised framework permit, providing a link for downloading the documents. Thea responded that she did not receive the email and requested clarification. The initial email included details about revisions to the plans for the Nordelva crossing and updated information on emission permits.Ihuga AS has submitted a framework application for Phase 1 of the Arctic Center ski resort in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn. The application seeks permission for the construction of various facilities including parking, roads, a welcome center, a top cafe, lifts, slopes, lift houses, and landscaping.\n\nArctic Center AS har sendt inn en rammes\u00f8knad for etablering av Fase 1 av et nytt skisenter i H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn. Prosjektet inkluderer blant annet et parkeringsanlegg, vei og tekniske anlegg, velkomstsenter, toppkafe, heiser og nedfarter. Det er ogs\u00e5 planlagt terrengbearbeidelser i omr\u00e5dene 1, 2 og 3, samt etablering av vann- og avl\u00f8psl\u00f8sninger. Toppstasjonen av skisenteret ligger p\u00e5 Botnfjellet, 884 moh.\n\nSummary: The ski center phase 1 is located in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn on Kval\u00f8ya, with the top station at Botnfjellet at 884 meters above sea level. The project is in accordance with the current zoning plans 1875 and 1515. The majority of the project falls within plan 1875, with only the chairlift route 1 and its infrastructure, access roads, ski slopes, and top station falling under plan 1515. The current zoning plans and related documents can be accessed on the municipality's website.\n\nReguleringsplan 1875 er tilgjengelig p\u00e5 kommunens nettsider. En rammes\u00f8knad for Arctic Center fase 1 inkluderer et velkomstsenter ved bunnen av skianlegget og en kaf\u00e9 p\u00e5 toppen av Botnfjellet. Velkomstsenteret har fire plan med ulike funksjoner, mens kafeen har to plan og er tilknyttet en stolheis. Toppen av velkomstsenteret ligger p\u00e5 h\u00f8yde 70 meter over havet og vil ha trekledning som hovedmateriale.\n\nThe plan includes the construction of a top caf\u00e9 at an elevation of 842.5 meters above sea level, with serving and seating areas as well as a sheltered terrace. The caf\u00e9 is regulated by plan 1515. Additionally, a welcome center is planned at the base of the ski resort, with four levels including facilities for ski rental, shops, administration, and public functions. The welcome center will have a facade primarily made of wood.\n\nThe text describes plans for a cafe at the top of Botnfjellet mountain, connected to the top station of a ski lift. The cafe will have two floors, with the lower floor containing amenities like entrance, toilets, and storage, and the upper floor housing seating areas and a terrace. The design of the cafe must adhere to regulations outlined in plan 1515, including a maximum building height of 5 meters and the use of local materials like natural stone. The overall aim is to create a tourist facility that blends in with the natural surroundings and maximizes the use of the landscape.\n\nThe application for the Arctic Center Phase 1 includes designs for the east and south facades of the building. The cafe is designed as a simple volume that rises from the south entrance towards the north, becoming narrower. The building will be clad with stone from the top and greyed wood, creating a subdued expression despite large windows. The roof will be covered with the same type of wood as the sides. An entryway has a large covered area for protection from snow and weather. The ground floor is raised 40-80 cm above the terrain for protection from snow and creates a visual experience of floating over the landscape. Access to the entrance will be built to blend with the terrain. Parking facilities will be located within designated areas and will be replaced by buildings in later phases.\n\nI fase 1 av prosjektet er forplassen og parkeringer trukket mot FT1 for \u00e5 begrense inngrepene p\u00e5 infrastrukturen. Kafeen er utformet som et volum som stiger fra s\u00f8r mot nord og vil bli kledt med stein og gr\u00e5net treverk. Inngangen vil ha et st\u00f8rre overdekket omr\u00e5de for \u00e5 skjerme mot sn\u00f8, v\u00e6r og vind. Gulvet i f\u00f8rste etasje er l\u00f8ftet over terreng for \u00e5 beskytte mot sn\u00f8 og f\u00f8yke. Adkomsten vil tilpasses terrenget, og parkeringsanlegget vil bli etablert innenfor angitte omr\u00e5der.\n\nParkeringsplasser innenfor KA2, N2 og N3 vil bli erstattet av bebyggelse i senere faser. I fase 1 er forplass og parkeringer plassert mot FT1 for \u00e5 begrense inngrepene for veiinfrastruktur. Seks skiheiser, inkludert bamseb\u00e5nd, T-krok, koppheis og stolheiser, etableres i fase 1 med integrerte heishus p\u00e5 bunn og toppstasjon. Tre heishus vil ogs\u00e5 bli oppf\u00f8rt ved bunnene av andre heiser med enhetlig utforming. De fleste heisene ligger innenfor plan 1875.\n\nThe T6 ski lift, lift house, top station, and associated technology are within plan 1515. T7 is only within plan 1515. Drawings of lift houses and routes are attached. In phase 1, six ski lifts are established: T1, T2, T4, T5, T6, and T7. Different types of lifts are used for each, such as surface lifts, T-bars, and chairlifts. T6 and T7 have integrated lift houses at the bottom and top stations. Other lifts will have separate lift houses. T1, T2, T3, and T5 are within plan 1875, while T6 and T7 have parts within plan 1875 and 1515. Drawings of lift houses and routes are included. Permission is sought for the establishment of a new chairlift with lift houses at the bottom and top.\n\nDet s\u00f8kes om tillatelse for etablering av en ny stolheis, med heishus b\u00e5de i bunnen og p\u00e5 toppen, med samme design og utforming som Stolheis 1. Heisen vil v\u00e6re ca 1465 meter lang og vil ligge innenfor form\u00e5let skitrekk. Det s\u00f8kes ogs\u00e5 om dispensasjon for \u00e5 flytte mellomstasjonene h\u00f8yere opp i fjellet for \u00e5 redusere lengden p\u00e5 topptrekket med ca 540 meter. Nabovarsel gjelder begge alternative plasseringer av mellomstasjonen.\n\nIn connection with a building application, permission is sought to move the intermediate stations higher in the mountains to a more suitable area for the stations. This would reduce the length of the ski lift by approximately 540 meters. The attached neighbor notification applies to both alternative placements. Additionally, in Phase 1, ski slopes associated with lifts T1, T2, T4, T5, T6, and T7 will be established, with some slopes located outside of the designated area. An access road will be needed for the construction of the lifts and associated infrastructure, with the exact location to be specified later.\n\nExisting access road to the parking area was surveyed, approved, and developed in 2016, 2017. In connection with phase 1 AC, there is a request for the establishment of a road to the parking area and internal roads further into the parking area up to arrival areas.\n\nA well-functioning and crossing of \"Nordelva\" is crucial for the overall flow in the alpine areas. In the main crossing, there will be traffic to both the bottom area and the start of chairlift 1. The capacity of the main chairlift in phase 1 is a maximum of 3,000 people per hour. The base station and slopes to the lift are on opposite sides of the river. Due to capacity reasons, an extended crossing and functional solution are needed that also accommodates the crossing of the cross-country ski trail.\n\nIn phase 1, the ski slopes connected to lifts T1, T2, T4, T5, T6, and T7 will be established. The slopes connected to T6 and T7 are mostly outside of plan 1875 but within 1515.\n\nDet er behov for anleggsvei i forbindelse med etablering av heiser og infrastruktur. Veier og adkomstveier m\u00e5 godkjennes og opparbeides, og en viktig krysning av Nordelva m\u00e5 planlegges for \u00e5 ivareta trafikk og flyt i alpinomr\u00e5dene. Det vil v\u00e6re behov for en utvidet krysning for \u00e5 ivareta kapasiteten og funksjonaliteten i omr\u00e5det.\n\nFigur 18 og 19 viser planer og tidligere illustrasjoner av flere krysninger, spesielt krysningen av Nordelva, som ble grundigere diskutert i s\u00f8knad dispensasjon. Figur 20 viser en illustrasjon av krysningen over Nordelva, med redegj\u00f8relser for terrenginngrepene knyttet til hovedkrysningen.\n\nIllustrasjon av krysning over Nordelva er en del av en rammes\u00f8knad for Arctic Center Fase 1. Det er planlagt terrenginngrep for krysningen av Nordelva, inkludert etablering av bunnstasjon for en stolheis, kulvert for elv og skil\u00f8pere, samt terrengarronderinger. Dette omr\u00e5det er viktig for sammenheng og flyt i skisenteret, og det er n\u00f8dvendig med terrengtilpasninger og infrastruktur for \u00e5 sikre riktig fall og oversiktlighet.\n\nOmr\u00e5de 2 omhandler terrengtilpasninger rundt velkomstsenteret, skitorget, vareleveringsomr\u00e5det og sk\u00f8ytebanen med behov for store terrengbearbeidelser p\u00e5 grunn av opptil 6 meter h\u00f8ydeforskjell. Omr\u00e5de 3 omhandler parkeringsomr\u00e5det som ligger i hellende terreng med behov for terrengarronderinger p\u00e5 opptil 3 meter for \u00e5 im\u00f8tekomme krav til stigningsforhold og siktlinjer for busser. Reguleringsplanen fokuserer p\u00e5 bevaring av eksisterende terreng og vegetasjon, men det er behov for st\u00f8rre terrenginngrep i tre omr\u00e5der i forbindelse med etablering av Fase 1 Arctic Center.\n\nOmr\u00e5de 1: Utbygging av infrastruktur ved Nordelva for \u00e5 etablere bunnstasjon for en stolheis, kulvert for elv og skil\u00f8pere, samt terrengarronderinger. Dette omr\u00e5det er viktig for flyten i skisenteret og krever riktig fall, oversiktlighet og infrastruktur. Det vil v\u00e6re behov for terrengtilpasninger og kulvert-etablering.\n\nOmr\u00e5de 2: Tilpasninger rundt velkomstsenteret med forplassen, skitorget, vareleveringsomr\u00e5det og sk\u00f8ytebanen. Det er behov for terrengbearbeidelser for \u00e5 tilrettelegge logistikk med adkomst for kj\u00f8ret\u00f8y, busser, gjester, varelevering og avfallshenting.\n\nOmr\u00e5de 3: Tilrettelegging av parkeringsomr\u00e5de i hellende terreng med behov for terrengarronderinger for rasjonelle parkeringsomr\u00e5der og adkomstveier for busser, avfallsbiler og annen transport. Strenge krav til stigningsforhold og siktlinjer for busser. Terrengendringene kan bli opptil 3 meter i enkelte omr\u00e5der.\n\nSummary: This document provides information on ongoing discussions with the Labor Inspectorate, an agreement with REMIKS for waste management, and plans for fire protection and pedestrian/cycling access from the county road to the site.\n\nA path/walkway is being constructed and extended over the dam from the mini power plant according to the attached master plan. This project will affect properties 66/4 and 66/3, with most of the infrastructure being established on property 66/4. Parts of ski lift T6 and associated infrastructure will be established on property 68/3, along with the top station for the chair lift. Additionally, a welcome center and two lift houses will be established within area T1. The footprint of the welcome center is 935 m2, the footprint of lift house 1 is 2 x 25 m2, and the total within area T1 is 985 m2. The plan also includes the construction of lift house 3 and the base station for the chair lift within the ski area, with a total footprint of 233 m2. The top station for chair lifts 1 and 2 and base station for chair lift 2 are located within area 6.1. Skilift, plan 1515.\n\nThe utilization rates for the area are not specified. The footprint of the top station of Ski lift 1 is 208 m2, while the footprint of the bottom station of Ski lift 2 is also 208m2. The total footprint is 624 m2 with Ski lift 2 and 416 m2 without Ski lift 2. The top station of Ski lift 2 is within area T2 with a footprint of 208 m2 and a usable area of 25 m2. The top caf\u00e9 has a footprint of 137 m2 and a utilization rate of 5% within area T2. The developments in phase 1 affect properties 66/4 and 66/3, with most of the infrastructure on property 66/4. Property 68/3 will have part of Ski lift T6 and associated infrastructure, access road, and the top floor of the ski lift. The welcome center and two ski lift houses are within area T1 with a total footprint of 985 m2 and a utilization rate of 4%. Ski lift 3 and the bottom station of the ski lift are within the ski resort area 1410 with a total area of about 5060.\n\nTotalt fotavtrykk for heishusene er 233 m2, med bunnstasjon p\u00e5 208 m2 og toppstasjon p\u00e5 25 m2. Fotavtrykket for stolheisene er 624 m2 med Stolheis 2 og 416 m2 uten Stolheis 2. Tillatt utnyttelsesgrad for omr\u00e5det er 5% med en total tomteareal p\u00e5 3249 m2. Toppkaf\u00e9en har et fotavtrykk p\u00e5 137 m2 og en BRA p\u00e5 163 m2, mens heishuset har en BRA p\u00e5 25 m2. Totalt utnyttet areal i T2-omr\u00e5det er 5% av BRA.\n\nThe document discusses the application for a building permit for the Arctic Center Phase 1, specifically regarding a dispensation request from certain zoning regulations. The request is related to the need for adjustments to the terrain and extending a crossing over the Nordelva river to accommodate a ski lift and slopes. This extension beyond the regulated 20-meter limit is necessary due to the layout of the area and to maintain flow and capacity. The existing cross-country ski trail also crosses through this area.\n\nDet \u00f8nskes \u00e5 f\u00f8re alpintraseen over langrennsl\u00f8ypen for \u00e5 skape en sikker krysning mellom langrenn og alpint, samtidig som antall krysningspunkter mellom de to aktivitetene \u00f8nskes redusert. En utvidelse av krysningspunktet og bruk av kulvert vil medf\u00f8re st\u00f8rre terrengendringer enn bruk av bru, men en l\u00f8sning med bru vil kreve flere krysninger og st\u00f8rre inngrep i terrenget. L\u00f8sningen med brukonstruksjoner antas \u00e5 gi d\u00e5rligere alpinprodukt, sikkerhet og flyt i omr\u00e5det p\u00e5 lengre sikt. Fordelene med \u00e5 gi dispensasjon fra reguleringsplanen anses som flere og bedre enn ulempene.\n\nDet er behov for terrengtilpasninger og utvidelse av krysningen over Nordelva til stolheis 1 og nedfarter, utover 20 meter. Reguleringsplanen inkluderer flere krysninger av Nordelva, og for \u00e5 kompensere for en krysning som er tatt ut, m\u00e5 en gjenv\u00e6rende krysning utvides. Det er \u00f8nskelig \u00e5 f\u00f8re alpintraseen over langrennsl\u00f8ypen for \u00e5 skape en sikker krysning mellom langrenn og alpint, og redusere antall krysningspunkter. Fordeler og ulemper av ulike l\u00f8sninger inkluderer terrengendringer og inngrep for konstruksjoner ved bruk av kulvert eller brokonstruksjoner, samt behov for arronderinger av landskap for langrennsl\u00f8yper og alpintraseer.\n\nEn l\u00f8sning med brukonstruksjoner vil f\u00f8re til st\u00f8rre fysiske og visuelle terrengendringer, d\u00e5rligere alpinprodukt, sikkerhet og flyt i omr\u00e5det. Det vil ogs\u00e5 kreve nye tiltak n\u00e5r anlegget vokser. En alternativ skissert l\u00f8sning vil gi det beste funksjonelle tilbudet og konsentrere aktivitet og flyt i et punkt for \u00e5 begrense behovet for endringer. Fordelene ved \u00e5 gi dispensasjon for denne l\u00f8sningen antas \u00e5 v\u00e6re st\u00f8rre enn ulempene.\n\nThis text is discussing applications for dispensation from the regulations of a specific development plan for the construction of a ski center. The dispensations are requested for the crossing of Nordelva H410_7 as a bridge structure and for adjustments in the placement of ski lifts to optimize the ski resort layout and efficiency.\n\nMindre justeringer gj\u00f8res innenfor samme form\u00e5lsomr\u00e5der og retninger, blant annet justeres plasseringen av \"Bytrekket\" i bunnen mens den beholdes i \u00f8vre del innenfor hensynssonen. Heiser som var vist og plassert p\u00e5 et overordnet niv\u00e5 i reguleringsprosessen m\u00e5 endres noe p\u00e5 grunn av detaljering og videre utvikling av anlegget. Endringene vil ikke ha negative effekter, men vil optimalisere og forbedre arealbruk og funksjonen som reguleringsplanen legger opp til. Fordelene med dispensasjonen vil derfor v\u00e6re st\u00f8rre enn eventuelle ulemper. Dispensasjoner s\u00f8kes blant annet for krysning av Nordelva som skal utf\u00f8res som brukonstruksjon, og plassering av heistrase med hensyn til infrastruktur uten st\u00f8rre terrenginngrep enn n\u00f8dvendig for fundamentering av heismaster.\n\nDet er n\u00f8dvendig med mindre justeringer og dispensasjon fra hensynssoner for \u00e5 optimalisere skianlegget og heistraseer. Endringene vil forbedre arealbruk og funksjonen som reguleringen legger opp til, uten negative effekter. Justeringer er n\u00f8dvendige for \u00e5 oppn\u00e5 dette, og fordelene med dispensasjonen vil v\u00e6re st\u00f8rre enn mulige ulemper.\n\nThis is a document related to a planning application for the Artic Center Phase 1, with figures showing the positioning of certain areas (T1, T2, T5) in the center. There is also a request for a dispensation regarding the establishment of a turning hammer for delivery and waste collection in the welcome center. The dispensation is required as it may conflict with the designated area for the alpine trail. The need for a turning hammer is due to logistical reasons and to ensure access is not obstructed.\n\nAn application for dispensation is being made to establish a welcome center with associated functions for delivery of goods and waste collection. The dispensation is needed to create a turning area for delivery vehicles within the designated ski area, as access must be provided without conflicting with ski slopes and products. The dispensation is necessary to allow the establishment of the welcome center with its functions while ensuring that access and use of the lower level are separate from public access areas.\n\nDriftsarealene er avhengige av tilkomst, og fordelene ved \u00e5 gi dispensasjonen for adkomst til disse arealene vil v\u00e6re st\u00f8rre enn fordelene ved \u00e5 ikke gi dispensasjonen. Det er viktig \u00e5 skille mellom publikumsadkomst og varelevering/driftsadkomst. Det s\u00f8kes ogs\u00e5 om dispensasjon for etablering av en gang sykkeltrase ved \u00e5 flytte den til nedkanten av parkeringen for bedre tilgjengelighet.\n\nDet s\u00f8kes om dispensasjon for \u00e5 flytte en gang/sykkelvei til en annen plassering for \u00e5 redusere arealinngrepene i omr\u00e5det. Dette vil gi bedre effektivitet, opplevelse og produkt. Det antas \u00e5 v\u00e6re f\u00e5 negative konsekvenser, og fordelene ved dispensasjonen vil v\u00e6re st\u00f8rre enn ulempene. Dispensasjonen vil ogs\u00e5 gj\u00f8re det mulig \u00e5 lagre sn\u00f8 i omr\u00e5det for br\u00f8yting i vinterhalv\u00e5ret, etter \u00e5 ha oppdaget en inkurie i tidligere henvisninger til omr\u00e5dets bruk. Dispensasjon vil v\u00e6re n\u00f8dvendig for \u00e5 etablere gang- og sykkelvei p\u00e5 et omr\u00e5de regulert til \"gr\u00f8nnstruktur-kombinerte form\u00e5l\".\n\nDet s\u00f8kes om dispensasjon fra reguleringsform\u00e5let GAA2 for \u00e5 flytte en gang- og sykkelvei i forbindelse med et skisenter. Flyttingen vil redusere arealinngrepene i omr\u00e5det og forbedre effektiviteten og opplevelsen. Det ansees \u00e5 ha f\u00e5 negative konsekvenser, og fordelene ved dispensasjonen vil v\u00e6re st\u00f8rre. I tillegg er det tillatt \u00e5 lagre sn\u00f8 i omr\u00e5der avsatt til gr\u00f8nnstruktur i vinterhalv\u00e5ret.\n\nThe area is planned to be used for snow storage for plowing, primarily for the adjacent parking lot. Establishing a pedestrian and bicycle path on land designated for \"green structure-combined purposes\" will require a dispensation from the designated use. Dispensation is being sought to modify the location of ski lift stations in order to improve operational efficiency and wind protection.\n\nDispensation is being sought from the regulations in order to adjust the location of ski lift stations and improve skiing conditions in windy areas. The goal is to extend one ski lift and shorten another, as well as to bring the stations closer together for operational and commercial reasons. This flexibility will allow for better ski conditions and increased commercial opportunities.\n\nDispensasjonen tillater etableringen av en toppstasjon for en stolheis innenfor et omr\u00e5de avsatt til et skianlegg, samt en del av en bunnstasjon for en annen stolheis p\u00e5 samme omr\u00e5de. Den totale mengden heis-infrastruktur vil v\u00e6re uendret, men det vil legge til rette for mer effektiv bruk av eksisterende strukturer og \u00f8ke muligheten for sambruk av omr\u00e5der knyttet til de to stasjonene. Fordelene inkluderer bedre driftsforhold, \u00f8kt brukeropplevelse og bedre kommersielle muligheter, mens ulempene er minimale og hovedsakelig knyttet til visuelle endringer i landskapet. Fordelene ved \u00e5 gi dispensasjon vurderes som langt st\u00f8rre og bedre enn ulempene.\n\nDispensasjon s\u00f8kes for \u00e5 justere plasseringen av topp- og bunnstasjonen av en skitrekk i omr\u00e5de T2 for \u00e5 oppn\u00e5 bedre drift, opplevelse, infrastruktur og kommersielle muligheter. Dispensasjonen vil ikke endre den totale mengden av heis-infrastruktur, men vil tillate mer fleksibilitet i bruk av eksisterende strukturer og \u00f8ke sambruk av arealer. Fordelene inkluderer bedre driftseffektivitet, reduserte kostnader, og forbedret opplevelse for gjestene, mens ulempene er minimale og hovedsakelig knyttet til visuell p\u00e5virkning av fjellet.\n\n\n\nThe request is for dispensation from current regulations in order to establish a better commercial offer and service functions with reduced impact on the environment. This includes improved options for skiers on windy days, increased predictability for users and operators, and benefits outweighing drawbacks. The dispensation is specifically sought for the construction of a lift house and top cafe within a designated area in a plan, as these facilities aim to enhance the overall experience and attractiveness of the location.\n\nThe caf\u00e9 is located in the basement and does not block the view. The top caf\u00e9 offers 360-degree views but has limited space and a need for support functions, which may obstruct important sight lines. To provide exceptional experiences within area T2, additional construction may be necessary for storage, technical installations, and support functions. While more construction would improve the overall product and experience, it may limit the visual impact of the building. The negative aspect of granting a dispensation would mainly be related to aesthetics. The caf\u00e9 and chair lift should be located in close proximity to each other to ensure a cohesive experience. It is important to consider how the building fits into the landscape and its interaction with outdoor areas. Insufficient space for functions may result in cluttered surroundings.\n\nThe regulation applies mainly to the size of the top cafe, not the elevator functions. The benefits of granting an exemption are believed to outweigh the drawbacks. A dispensation is sought from the planning regulations regarding documentation requirements for sewage systems. The desired solution for the water and sewage system at Arctic Center is based on infiltration, but an emissions permit and infiltration test are needed to meet the documentation requirements. The building must have a footprint of approximately 1000m2 and a maximum height of 5m above the surrounding terrain, with materials and colors that blend in with the natural surroundings. Rock from the area must be used in construction, and careful consideration must be given to the landscape. The building's utilization rate must not exceed 5%.\n\nDet s\u00f8kes om dispensasjon fra gjeldende utnyttelsesgrad for \u00e5 etablere b\u00e5de heishus til Stolheis 2 og en toppkafe innenfor omr\u00e5de T2 i plan 1515. Heishuset har begrenset st\u00f8rrelse mens kafeen trenger flere st\u00f8ttefunksjoner. Det \u00f8nskes en velfungerende kafe og attraktive opplevelser hele \u00e5ret. Fordeler med etableringen inkluderer tilknytning til skisenteret og nordlysopplevelser, men ulemper inkluderer at flere siktlinjer kan bli stengt. Det b\u00f8r tilbys eksepsjonelle opplevelser og tjenester i omr\u00e5det, med hensyn til drift og hel\u00e5rsdrift.\n\nVed \u00e5 tillate mer bebyggelse vil produktet, opplevelsen og helheten bli bedre, men det visuelle inntrykket av bygget vil v\u00e6re begrenset. Dispensasjonen det s\u00f8kes om er knyttet til st\u00f8rrelsen p\u00e5 toppkafeen og ikke heisfunksjonene. Det argumenteres for at fordelene ved \u00e5 gi dispensasjon er st\u00f8rre enn ulempene. Dispensasjonen som s\u00f8kes om gjelder dokumentasjonskrav for avl\u00f8psanlegg.\n\nIn the planning of the best water and sewage solution for Arctic Center, several alternative solutions have been considered and the preferred solution is based on infiltration. To obtain a discharge permit, an infiltration test must be carried out. However, the test cannot be conducted until at least May due to the need for bare ground and open terrain. Meetings have been held with the Water and Sewage section to finalize the approval process, with only the infiltration test remaining before the permit can be issued. The proposed solution includes advanced sewage treatment before infiltration, which has been well-received by the authorities. The submission of a foundation permit application is planned for May 2023, so a request is made to move certain documentation requirements to the building permit application.\n\nInfiltrasjonstesten vil bli utf\u00f8rt s\u00e5 snart forholdene tillater det, og resultatene vil bli sendt til kommunen. Byggesaken st\u00e5r n\u00e5 i bero p\u00e5 grunn av behov for barmark for \u00e5 utf\u00f8re testen. Det er viktig for fremdrift og kontinuitet i prosessen at behandlingen av byggesaken ikke tar for lang tid. Det er ingen risiko for kommunen \u00e5 flytte kravet om utslippstillatelse til brukstillatelse, da dette uansett m\u00e5 foreligge f\u00f8r anlegget tas i bruk. En dispensasjon for \u00e5 utf\u00f8re testen er vurdert \u00e5 ha flere fordeler enn ulemper, da det er umulig \u00e5 gjennomf\u00f8re testen p\u00e5 n\u00e5v\u00e6rende tidspunkt p\u00e5 grunn av \u00e5rstiden.\n\nByggesaken vil bli satt p\u00e5 vent inntil infiltrasjonstesten er gjennomf\u00f8rt for \u00e5 klarlegge n\u00f8dvendig infiltrasjonsareal for en ny VA l\u00f8sning. Den planlagte h\u00f8ygradige rensingen av avl\u00f8psvannet har blitt positivt mottatt av vann og avl\u00f8psseksjonen. S\u00f8knad om IG for grunnarbeider og fundamenter er planlagt innsendt i mai 2023. Selv om det er uheldig at byggesaken n\u00e5 st\u00e5r i bero p\u00e5 grunn av behovet for barmarkssesongen for pr\u00f8ver, vil kontinuitet og effektivitet i saksbehandlingen v\u00e6re avgj\u00f8rende for fremdrift og kunnskapsformidling.\n\nKommunen s\u00f8ker dispensasjon for \u00e5 grave en vannledning i et omr\u00e5de avsatt til landbruk, natur og friluftsliv (LNFR) for vannforsyning til Arctic Center. Det hevdes at det ikke er noen risiko for kommunen \u00e5 flytte kravet om utslippstillatelse til brukstillatelse da dette uansett m\u00e5 foreligge f\u00f8r anlegget kan tas i bruk. Det p\u00e5pekes at det er en l\u00f8sning for vann, avl\u00f8p og overvann (VAO) som er oversendt kommunen, og at s\u00f8knaden om dispensasjon kun er knyttet til n\u00e5v\u00e6rende \u00e5rstid som gj\u00f8r det umulig \u00e5 utf\u00f8re n\u00f8dvendige tester. Det argumenteres for at fordelene ved \u00e5 gi dispensasjon oppveier ulempene.\n\nDet s\u00f8kes om dispensasjon for \u00e5 grave en vannledning innenfor et uregulert omr\u00e5de avsatt til LNFR i reguleringsplanen. Ledningen vil forsyne Arctic Center med vann fra et eksisterende kraftverk, og planen er valgt for \u00e5 unng\u00e5 inngrep i eksisterende damanlegg og redusere anleggsomfanget. Prosjektet inneb\u00e6rer graving av en ledningsgr\u00f8ft og kryssing av Nordelva med tradisjonell graving og reetablering av elvebunnen.\n\nEn ledningsgr\u00f8ft for en vannledning utenfor reguleringsplanen skal opprettes med masser reetablert med stedlige planter. En alternativ tras\u00e9 ville inneb\u00e6re gravearbeid ved demningen, men dette anses \u00e5 v\u00e6re mer risikofullt med negative konsekvenser for vannkvaliteten og dammen. NVE \u00f8nsker \u00e5 unng\u00e5 inngrep i tilknytning til demningen.\n\nEn alternativ tras\u00e9 er etablert for \u00e5 sikre bedre, tryggere og mer milj\u00f8vennlig vannforsyning. Prosjektet tar hensyn til LNFR-omr\u00e5dets form\u00e5l med \u00e5 sikre natur, rekreasjon og friluftsliv. Vannledningen vil ha minimal innvirkning p\u00e5 et n\u00e6rliggende fortidsminne, og alternativet med \u00e5 ta vann direkte fra dammen anses som mer risikabelt med st\u00f8rre negative konsekvenser for vannkvaliteten og milj\u00f8et. For \u00e5 unng\u00e5 inngrep i tilknytning til demningen er den alternative traseen valgt som den beste l\u00f8sningen.\n\nHensikten med et LNFR-omr\u00e5de er \u00e5 sikre natur, rekreasjon og friluftsliv. Etableringen av en vannledning medf\u00f8rer et lite inngrep som vil ha ubetydelige spor over tid og synes \u00e5 v\u00e6re lite i konflikt med gjeldende arealform\u00e5l. Fordelene ved \u00e5 gi dispensasjon anses \u00e5 v\u00e6re flere og bedre enn ulempene. Vannledningen er plassert i god avstand til et fortidsminne og vil ikke p\u00e5virke det. Dokumentasjonskrav til rammes\u00f8knaden inkluderer godkjenning fra Mattilsynet og forurensningsmyndighet, hvor det er s\u00f8kt dispensasjon fra noen av kravene.\n\nIn order to obtain planning permission or a start-up permit, approval of a permit application to establish a private water and sewage system is required. Additionally, a waste management plan must be included in the planning application. Approval from the Fylkesmannen in Troms and Finnmark for a solution for water treatment or infiltration is necessary before a start-up permit can be granted. A rigging and ground safety plan with intervention limits must also be in place before a planning permit can be issued.\n\nDet skal beskrives hvordan terrenginngrep skal utf\u00f8res sk\u00e5nsomt, med fokus p\u00e5 minimale fyllinger og skj\u00e6ringer, gode overganger til tilst\u00f8tende terreng og unng\u00e5else av s\u00e5r i terrenget. Ber\u00f8rte omr\u00e5der skal revegeteres naturlig og stedegen masse skal benyttes. Det skal angis omr\u00e5der for midlertidig deponi, rigg og anleggsomr\u00e5de, samt oppstilling av maskiner og annet utstyr. Det kreves detaljerte landskaps- og vegetasjonsplaner samt istandsettingsplaner f\u00f8r rammetillatelse kan gis. Dokumentasjon er n\u00f8dvendig fra myndigheter ang\u00e5ende vannforsyning og avl\u00f8psanlegg f\u00f8r tillatelser kan gis. Vedlagt f\u00f8lger redegj\u00f8relser fra forskjellige instanser.\n\nEndringer er gjort i paragraf 14 til paragraf 13. Dispensasjon er s\u00f8kt for dokumentasjonskravet. En godkjenning fra Fylkesmannen i Troms og Finnmark er n\u00f8dvendig for etablering av privat vann- og avl\u00f8psanlegg. Renovasjonsplan og avtale med REMIKS er vedlagt s\u00f8knaden. Rammes\u00f8knaden m\u00e5 f\u00f8lge bestemte rekkef\u00f8lgekrav, inkludert godkjent l\u00f8sning for rensing eller infiltrasjon f\u00f8r igangsettingstillatelse kan gis. Rigging og marksikringsplan m\u00e5 ogs\u00e5 v\u00e6re p\u00e5 plass f\u00f8r rammetillatelse kan gis. Dispensasjon er s\u00f8kt for dokumentasjonskravet.\n\nDet m\u00e5 redegj\u00f8res for sk\u00e5nsomme terrenginngrep med minst mulig fyllinger og skj\u00e6ringer, gode overganger til tilst\u00f8tende terreng og naturlig revegetering av ber\u00f8rte omr\u00e5der. Det skal brukes stedegen masse, og omr\u00e5der for midlertidig deponi og anlegg skal angis. Det m\u00e5 ogs\u00e5 oppgis oppstilling av maskiner og utstyr, brakker og lagringsomr\u00e5der. Det kreves detaljerte landskaps- og vegetasjonsplaner f\u00f8r rammetillatelse kan gis. Det f\u00f8lger med landskaps- og vegetasjonsplaner samt redegj\u00f8relser fra J\u00f8rgensen Plankontor. En forh\u00e5ndskonferanse med kommunen ble avholdt, og visse tiltak anses \u00e5 utl\u00f8se s\u00f8knadsplikt og ansvarsrett, som bygninger som velkomstsenter, skihus og heiser.\n\nSummary:\nRegarding terrain alterations as a result of preparing ski slopes, the regulations state that existing terrain and vegetation should be preserved as much as possible, with any necessary alterations kept to a minimum. Significant terrain alterations require a permit, while smaller alterations in rural areas may be exempt from permitting requirements. The need for permits for structures such as buildings, ice rinks, and tents depends on factors such as size, materials, and intended use. Specific plans for ice and snow alterations were not included in the submitted application, but potential areas were marked on a map.\n\nKommunen \u00f8nsker \u00e5 sikre \u00e5penhet, forutsigbarhet og medvirkning i forbindelse med vurderingen av en ny VAO-l\u00f8sning. Trova AS er engasjert for \u00e5 vurdere l\u00f8sningen og har utarbeidet en redegj\u00f8relse. Det er sendt ut nabovarsel og mottatt en merknad. Landskaps- og vegetasjonsplaner er vedlagt. Temaer og tiltak er vurdert \u00e5 utl\u00f8se s\u00f8knadsplikt og ansvarsrett i forbindelse med bygninger som velkomstsenter, skihus og heiser.\n\nDette dokumentet om terrenginngrep fastsetter at eksisterende terreng og vegetasjon b\u00f8r i st\u00f8rst mulig grad bevares, og at st\u00f8rre terrenginngrep krever s\u00f8knad. Mindre terrenginngrep, som ikke f\u00f8rer til mer enn 3,0 meter avvik fra opprinnelig terrengniv\u00e5 i spredtbygd str\u00f8k, er unntatt s\u00f8knadsplikt. For andre innretninger som isbygninger, sk\u00f8ytebaner og lavvoer, m\u00e5 det gj\u00f8res en konkret vurdering for \u00e5 avgj\u00f8re om de er s\u00f8knadspliktige etter gjeldende regler. Det presiseres at det ikke er uttegnet konkrete tiltak i is og sn\u00f8 i s\u00f8knaden, men aktuelle omr\u00e5der er angitt p\u00e5 situasjonskartet.\n\nI forbindelse med en forh\u00e5ndskonferanse har kommunen bemerket at det b\u00f8r vurderes om en ny VAD-l\u00f8sning skal gjennomg\u00e5 en reguleringsprosess for \u00e5 sikre \u00e5penhet og medvirkning. Trava AS er engasjert for \u00e5 vurdere VAO-l\u00f8sningen og har utarbeidet en l\u00f8sning. Det er sendt ut nabovarsler, og det er mottatt merknader. Blant annet har det v\u00e6rt merknader fra Troms og Finnmark fylkeskommune, men disse regnes som en orientering. Nabovarsel 2 ble sendt ut, og det er registrert 8 merknader.\n\nI forbindelse med videre prosjektering og utvikling etter forh\u00e5ndskonferansen ble det konkludert med behov for \u00e5 etablere Stolheis 2 og kaf\u00e9 p\u00e5 toppen av Lille Bl\u00e5mann i fase 1. Det har v\u00e6rt endringer i parkeringsomr\u00e5dene og behov for \u00e5 varsle naboer om veinettet p\u00e5 nytt. Noen dispensasjoner ble varslet i varsel 2. Mottatte kommentarer til varsel 2 har hovedsakelig v\u00e6rt rettet mot VAO l\u00f8sning. VAO l\u00f8sningen er blitt revidert etter tilbakemeldinger fra kommunen. Kommentarer fra enkelte naboer er ikke lenger relevante da VAO l\u00f8sningen er i tr\u00e5d med gjeldende plan. En annen nabo har p\u00e5pekt krav til st\u00f8yskjerm mot deres eiendom i forbindelse med en annen godkjent plan. Dette vil bli fulgt opp som en egen byggesak.\n\nTunelv vil bli kontaktet ang\u00e5ende prosjektering, varsel og byggesak st\u00f8yskjerm. Trafikksikkerhet og vei/kryssl\u00f8sninger var sentrale temaer i reguleringsarbeidene for plan 1875. Utforming av kryss er i tr\u00e5d med planen. Andrea Schneider's merknader er ikke lenger relevante da VAO l\u00f8sningen er endret i henhold til gjeldende VAO rammeplan. Sylvi Irene Viken Johansen's merknader gir ingen konkrete anmerkninger. Nabovarsel 2 ble sendt ut 24. mars 2022 med endringer som inkluderer etablering av Stolheis 2 og kaf\u00e9 p\u00e5 toppen av Lille Bl\u00e5mann i fase 1, samt endringer av P-omr\u00e5der og behov for \u00e5 nabovarsle veitraseer p\u00e5 nytt. Dispensasjon 6, 7 og 8 ble ogs\u00e5 nabovarslet i varsel 2.\n\nMerknader til varsel 2 ble hovedsakelig rettet mot den varslede VAO l\u00f8sningen. Etter tilbakemeldinger fra kommunen ble VAO l\u00f8sningen revidert. Svarene p\u00e5 merknadene fra naboene viser at VAO l\u00f8sningen er n\u00e5 i tr\u00e5d med gjeldende rammeplan. Andre merknader ang\u00e5ende st\u00f8yskjerm og trafikksikkerhet vil bli fulgt opp som egne byggesaker.\n\nResponses from Ryeng, John Ola Johnsen, and Mikalsen Solveig Hennie indicate that the VAO solution has been changed based on feedback from neighbors and is now in line with the current VAO framework. Mikalsen Solveig Hennie's property 66/78 was assessed to not require shielding against noise or light from the ski center, and they see no need for this to change.\n\nSolveig Hennie Mikalsen, owner of property 66/78, does not believe there is a need for noise or light screening due to the proposed ski center. Andersen Ulf Tore, owner of properties 66/25 and 66/35, apologizes for the extensive neighbor notification regarding the Arctic Center project and notes that the VAO solution has been changed based on feedback, rendering some of his previous comments irrelevant. A new notification was sent out on 17.01 regarding a dispensation request for documentation requirements g and h.\n\nSeven comments have been received in 2023. \nBenn Henri Johnsen Molund from Straumsvegen 411 responds by stating that there is no need for a section in the neighbor notification to illustrate the dispensation being sought. They plan to send a clarification email to address misunderstandings. \nEirik Aronsen and Henriette Sofie Pettersen from Straumsvegen 411 and 428 respectively mention the establishment of noise screening as a requirement for the application IG. Arctic Center will contact them once the application is on public display. \nSylvi Irene Viken Johansen from Straumsvegen 364 comments on the neighbor notification concerning the dispensation from documentation requirements.\n\nDet er n\u00f8dvendig med godkjenning fra forurensningsmyndigheten f\u00f8r tillatelser kan innvilges for avl\u00f8psanlegg. Nabovarslet om etableringen av Arctic Center har blitt justert etter merknader og p\u00e5pekninger fra naboer. En tredje nabovarsel ang\u00e5r s\u00f8knad om dispensasjon fra dokumentasjonskrav, og det har blitt sendt 7 merknader i forbindelse med dette. En nabo p\u00e5peker at det ikke er utarbeidet snitt for \u00e5 illustrere dispensasjonss\u00f8knaden.\n\nThere have been misunderstandings and confusion among recipients regarding the context and status of the application, so a clarification email will be sent out. A previously planned VAO solution has been withdrawn in favor of a better solution approved by the VAO framework, which will not affect the Mo/und property. Noise screening against property 66/46 is a requirement for the application, and planning and dialogue will begin once the application is submitted for review. Arctic Center will contact those affected. A neighbor's comment about the establishment of the Arctic Center seems to be a general critique and resistance to the ski center's establishment, despite a lengthy process with the need for many clarifications along the way.\n\nAC is aware of Johansen's wishes and opinions throughout the process. Johansen's comments are generally critical of the establishment of Arctic Center and past planning processes. Valio, on the other hand, has withdrawn a previously planned solution for VAO as a result of feedback and internal evaluations. The current VAO solution aligns with plan 1875 and previous decisions. The neighbor notices regarding dispensation from documentation requirements only address specific issues related to this.\n\nForesp\u00f8rsler og kommentarer ang\u00e5ende trafikale forhold anses ikke relevant for varselet og dispensasjonen. Bygging av avl\u00f8psrenseanlegg med infiltrasjon planlegges for minimal p\u00e5virkning p\u00e5 grunnvannet. Naboer har gitt generell kritikk av Arctic Center, men innvendinger rettes ikke direkte mot dispensasjonss\u00f8knaden. Dispensasjonss\u00f8knad ang\u00e5r vannforsyning og en vannledning som vil krysse et omr\u00e5de. Svarfrist for merknader er satt, og eventuelle sp\u00f8rsm\u00e5l kan rettes til ansvarlig s\u00f8ker. Skisse av velkomstsenteret vedlegges s\u00f8knaden.The document is a request for more information regarding a permit application for a ski facility and sports hall in Troms\u00f8, Norway. The application was submitted by IHUGA AS on behalf of ARCTIC CENTER AS. The authorities need additional documentation before they can process the application, and the deadline to submit the missing information is May 7, 2022. The project will involve approximately 15-20 future employees and will include a ski facility on Kval\u00f8ya Island in Troms\u00f8. The work will involve caf\u00e9 operations, trail preparation, equipment maintenance, and retail tasks.\n\nArctic Center AS har s\u00f8kt om samtykke etter arbeidsmilj\u00f8loven for et tiltak som best\u00e5r av en stor bygning med verksted, butikk, lager, varmestue, cafe, kontorer, m\u00f8terom og andre fasiliteter. Arbeidstilsynet har bedt om mer dokumentasjon f\u00f8r de kan behandle s\u00f8knaden, og varsler om mulig avslag dersom informasjonen ikke blir levert innen fristen. Tiltaket omfatter et skianlegg og en idrettshall.\n\nThere is some uncertainty about the floor area (BRA) of the project. The total number of future employees will be around 15-20. The project involves a new ski resort located on Kval\u00f8ya, Troms\u00f8 municipality, with Artie Center AS as the developer and employer. Work processes will include running a cafe, grooming slopes, equipment preparation, and working in a shop. The facility will have various amenities such as a workshop, store, lounge, offices, restrooms, and changing rooms for employees. The application process is based on several documents provided by the applicant.\n\nThis is a list of PDF files related to a construction project. The text mentions the need for information on total area, ventilation, chemical health hazards, and noise. It also references regulations on workplace ventilation and climate control. The text includes references to various documents related to the project.\n\nSeveral PDF files are listed, each with a specific code. The text also mentions the need for information on total gross floor area, ventilation requirements, chemical health hazards, and noise levels for a welcome center project. It requests documentation showing that ventilation plans meet regulations and that indoor climate requirements are met.\n\nArbeidsplassforskriften stiller krav til tilfredsstillende ventilasjon p\u00e5 arbeidsplassen for \u00e5 sikre et godt inneklima. Veiledninger fra Arbeidstilsynet gir normer for ventilasjon og luftkvalitet, og balansert mekanisk ventilasjon anbefales generelt. Kravene er strenge og det er viktig \u00e5 dokumentere at ventilasjonsl\u00f8sningene oppfyller normene for \u00e5 sikre tilfredsstillende inneklima og luftkvalitet. Lenker til regelverket finnes p\u00e5 Arbeidstilsynets nettside.\n\nArbeidstilsynet krever fullt forsvarlige bygningsmessige forhold og beskyttelse mot kjemisk helsefare p\u00e5 arbeidsplassen. Det kreves tilstrekkelig dokumentasjon for \u00e5 oppfylle kravene for ventilasjon og reduksjon av kjemisk helsefare. Prosjekteringen av inneklima og ventilasjon m\u00e5 v\u00e6re fullf\u00f8rt i s\u00f8knaden.\n\nRequests for documentation and calculations with form 444 and air volume calculations (room schedule) to demonstrate that indoor climate and ventilation requirements are met. The Workplace Regulations require mechanical ventilation and process-adapted extraction in work areas to maintain safe levels of chemicals in the air. Guidelines from the Labour Inspectorate specify norms for satisfactory indoor climate and air quality, with balanced mechanical ventilation generally ensuring adequate air exchange for satisfactory indoor climate. The Labour Inspectorate does not specify solutions but requires documentation of plans to achieve satisfactory indoor climate regardless of the nature of work. Meeting the norms in the guidelines should typically fulfill requirements for indoor climate and air quality. Compliance with indoor climate requirements is strictly enforced.\n\nDenne informasjonen gir veiledning om kravene og hvordan de kan oppfylles, samt lenker til relevant regelverk ang\u00e5ende ventilasjon, inneklima, og krav til fysisk arbeidsmilj\u00f8. Det p\u00e5pekes at bygningsmessige forhold m\u00e5 v\u00e6re forsvarlige og arbeidstakere m\u00e5 sikres mot helseskader ved kjemikalieh\u00e5ndtering i henhold til arbeidsmilj\u00f8loven. Arbeidstilsynet har ikke f\u00e5tt tilstrekkelig informasjon om planene for \u00e5 redusere kjemisk helsefare i s\u00f8knaden. Det beskrives at det vil v\u00e6re noe forurensning i verksted og sliperom, med naturlig utlufting i verkstedet.\n\nDette handler om kravene til \u00e5 redusere kjemisk helsefare p\u00e5 arbeidsplasser i henhold til Arbeidsmilj\u00f8loven. Dette inkluderer \u00e5 velge bygningsmessige l\u00f8sninger for \u00e5 redusere risikoen for eksponering for kjemikalier og forurensning, inneslutte kjemiske prosesser s\u00e5 langt det er mulig, og ha tilgang til rent vann, n\u00f8ddusjer og \u00f8yenskyll i tilfelle eksponering for helsefarlige stoffer.\n\nDet anbefales \u00e5 ha fastmonterte \u00f8yedusjer i n\u00e6rheten av omr\u00e5der hvor etsende kjemikalier brukes, samt vaskemuligheter for arbeidstakere som kan bli eksponert for kreftfremkallende eller mutagene kjemikalier. Kjemikalier skal h\u00e5ndteres og oppbevares forsvarlig for \u00e5 unng\u00e5 helseskader og ulykker. Rom for oppbevaring av kjemikalier b\u00f8r ha egen ventilasjon og v\u00e6re dimensjonert etter mengden bruk p\u00e5 virksomheten. Kravene for \u00e5 redusere kjemisk helsefare forvaltes strengt, og n\u00e6rmere veiledning finnes p\u00e5 Arbeidstilsynet sin nettside.\n\nS\u00f8knaden omhandler problemet med forurensninger og bruk av kjemikalier p\u00e5 arbeidsplassen, spesielt i verksted og sliperom. Det ettersp\u00f8rres informasjon om hvilke forurensninger og kjemikalier som kan utgj\u00f8re en helserisiko, samt hvilke bygningsmessige tiltak som skal gjennomf\u00f8res for \u00e5 oppfylle kravene i Arbeidsmilj\u00f8loven. Det er krav om \u00e5 redusere kjemisk helsefare i samsvar med arbeidsplassforskriften, og bygningsmessige l\u00f8sninger skal bidra til \u00e5 minimere risikoen for at arbeidstakere utsettes for kjemikalier og forurensning. Kjemiske prosesser b\u00f8r innesluttes s\u00e5 langt det er mulig for \u00e5 beskytte arbeidstakernes helse.\n\nDet er viktig at det finnes mulighet for \u00e5 spyle med rent vann p\u00e5 arbeidssteder hvor helsefarlige stoffer h\u00e5ndteres, og at det er tilgang til n\u00f8ddusjer og \u00f8yedusjer i tilfelle eksponering. Kjemikalier m\u00e5 oppbevares forsvarlig for \u00e5 unng\u00e5 skader, brann eller eksplosjoner. Det b\u00f8r v\u00e6re egnede rom for oppbevaring av kjemikalier, med tilstrekkelig ventilasjon. Kravene for \u00e5 redusere kjemisk helsefare m\u00e5 f\u00f8lges n\u00f8ye.\n\nThe text provides guidance on requirements and how they can be met, with links to relevant regulations. It addresses health risks from chemical use, ventilation, and noise in the workplace. Specific focus is on the need for adequate measures to protect workers from excessive noise levels, with a request for documentation of building modifications to address noise requirements.\n\nKravene til beskyttelse mot st\u00f8y p\u00e5 arbeidsplassen er detaljert beskrevet i Arbeidsplassforskriften. Disse inkluderer krav om utforming av arbeidsplasser for \u00e5 unng\u00e5 svekkelse av \u00e5rv\u00e5kenhet, bruk av lydabsorberende materialer, og hensyn til st\u00f8y fra tekniske innretninger. Det anbefales \u00e5 fjerne eller isolere lydkilden for \u00e5 forebygge st\u00f8y, og tiltak m\u00e5 oppfylle grenseverdiene for st\u00f8y satt i forskriften om tiltaks- og grenseverdier. Disse grenseverdiene varierer basert p\u00e5 st\u00f8ygrupper og arbeidsforhold, og st\u00f8ybelastningen b\u00f8r reduseres til minst 10 desibel under tiltaksverdien for hver st\u00f8ygruppe. Absolutte grenseverdier er ogs\u00e5 oppgitt for hvor mye st\u00f8y arbeidstakere kan bli eksponert for.\n\nThe maximum daily exposure level is 85 decibels and the maximum peak sound pressure level is 130 decibels. The project must be designed to ensure that these limits are not exceeded. Measures must be taken to categorize different rooms based on their noise levels. Specific solutions must be chosen by the developer to meet the requirements. Workspaces should be designed to prevent adverse physical effects on workers and ensure their health, safety, and welfare. There is not enough information to confirm that the workspaces will protect individual workstations from noise according to the regulations. There may be some noise associated with activities in the workshop and garage, but what measures will be taken to reduce the risk of health damage is not specified.\n\nArbeidstilsynet krever dokumentasjon p\u00e5 spesifikke bygningsmessige tiltak for \u00e5 ivareta kravene til st\u00f8ybeskyttelse p\u00e5 arbeidsplassen. Forskrifter og grenseverdier angir krav til beskyttelse mot st\u00f8y, og tiltakshaver m\u00e5 velge l\u00f8sninger som oppfyller disse kravene. Kommunen kan ikke gi igangsettingstillatelse uten samtykke fra Arbeidstilsynet. Det er viktig \u00e5 dokumentere at alle arbeidsplasser er beskyttet mot st\u00f8y i tr\u00e5d med regelverket. Arbeidsgivere skal sikre medvirkning fra arbeidstakerne i samtykkebehandlingen, og dokumentasjonen skal sendes via eDialog.TroVA AS has received a letter from Sametinget regarding the construction of the \"Arctic Center\" and the potential impact on a cultural heritage site. Sametinget is concerned that the planned construction could damage the heritage site and is advising that a special permit must be obtained to intervene in automatic heritage sites. TroVA AS has taken measures to protect the heritage site, including maintaining a distance of 20 meters between the construction and the site, creating a safety plan, and marking the boundary of the construction area. The company believes they have met the requirements and notes that the planned construction has already been approved through a previous plan. A copy of the letter has been sent to Troms\u00f8 municipality's building department and Arctic Center AS.Geir Johnsen is following up on a previous email sent to the Troms\u00f8 municipality regarding questions about the Arctic Center AS and the VAO-Rammeplan. They have not received a response and are seeking clarification on whether their input has been registered. They also have specific concerns about the impact of the new plan on their property and water supply, and are requesting that the municipality address these issues.Det s\u00f8kes om dispensasjon fra reguleringsplan 1875 for dokumentasjonskrav G ang\u00e5ende avl\u00f8psanlegg, som krever en utslippstillatelse. P\u00e5 grunn av behovet for barmark er det ikke mulig \u00e5 utf\u00f8re n\u00f8dvendige tester f\u00f8r tidligst i mai, noe som f\u00f8rer til at byggesaken settes p\u00e5 vent. Det argumenteres for at det er hensiktsmessig \u00e5 flytte kravet om utslippstillatelse til s\u00f8knad om igangsettingstillatelse for \u00e5 optimalisere prosessen. Kommunen anses \u00e5 ikke ha noen risiko ved \u00e5 godkjenne dispensasjonen. Samlet sett mener s\u00f8keren at fordelene ved \u00e5 gi dispensasjonen oppveier ulempene.Anders Koller Tufte thanked Thea Solvoll Liahjell for the decision from Statsforvalteren which overturned the municipality's decision due to a lack of a new hearing round after changes to the application. Thea Solvoll Liahjell, a lawyer in the Urban Development and Building Section of Troms\u00f8 municipality, sent the decision to Anders Koller Tufte following their phone call discussing the background for the new hearing round.The document is a letter regarding the establishment of the ski center \"Arctic Center\" in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn, Troms\u00f8 municipality. The Sami Parliament comments on the preservation of Sami cultural heritage and mentions that dialogue with reindeer management is necessary. The area was inspected in 2018 and 46 automatically protected Sami cultural heritage sites were identified. Concerns were raised regarding potential conflicts with cultural heritage during initial planning, but after further details were provided on the water pipeline installation method using horizontal drilling, it was deemed unlikely to impact the cultural heritage site. The document is signed electronically by Bj\u00f8rn Berg and Jon Gunnar Blom.Sametinget opprettholder sin uttalelse ang\u00e5ende dispensasjonss\u00f8knad for vannledning ved Arctic Center, da det inneb\u00e6rer konflikt med et automatisk fredet kulturminne. Tiltaket kan ikke godkjennes f\u00f8r det er s\u00f8kt om og fattet vedtak i dispensasjonssaken, og arkeologisk unders\u00f8kelse av kulturminnet m\u00e5 gjennomf\u00f8res. Referanse gis til uttalelse fra Statsforvalteren i Troms og Finnmark. Bj\u00f8rn Berg og Jon Gunnar Blom fra Sametinget er ansvarlige for saken.Thea Solvoll Liahjell sent an email to Svein Lian providing an offer for consultation and attachments of two consultation requests related to the Arctic Center case. She also mentioned a pleasant phone conversation and invited Lian to ask any additional questions. The email was signed by Thea Solvoll Liahjell, a lawyer from the Section for Urban Development, Building Affairs at the Troms\u00f8 municipality.Anders Koller Tufte is responding to a letter from Troms fylkeskommune regarding a revised application. The email includes an attachment with the response to the fylkeskommune. The email also mentions that they were not copied on the original email from Troms fylkeskommune, but they can provide their input if desired. The email is signed by Thea Solvoll Liahjell, a jurist at Troms\u00f8 kommune.Arbeidstilsynet har mottatt en s\u00f8knad om samtykke for et skianlegg og en idrettshall i Troms\u00f8. De har bedt om flere opplysninger for \u00e5 kunne behandle s\u00f8knaden, men har ikke mottatt svar innen fristen. Hvis opplysningene ikke blir sendt innen en ny frist, vil s\u00f8knaden bli avsl\u00e5tt, og fullt gebyr m\u00e5 betales. Arbeidsgiver skal informere arbeidstakerne om saken, og det sendes kopi av brevet til Troms\u00f8 kommune. Klageadgang er mulig innen tre dager etter \u00e5 ha mottatt brevet. Mer informasjon om krav til det fysiske arbeidsmilj\u00f8et kan finnes p\u00e5 Arbeidstilsynets nettsider.Anders Tufte sent a response to Thea Solvoll Liahjell regarding a neighbor notification for plan 1875 - Troms\u00f8 Arctic Center, with an attachment titled \"Svar p\u00e5 nabovarsel arctic center ihuga.docx.\" Ane Elene Johansen also sent a response to Tufte, providing her information as a tenant and the daughter of the property owners.Denne e-posten er fra Norges vassdrags- og energidirektorat (NVE) ang\u00e5ende en oppdatert s\u00f8knad om etablering av skianlegget Arctic Center i Troms\u00f8 kommune. NVE gir r\u00e5d og veiledning om hvordan nasjonale og regionale interesser knyttet til vassdrag og energiproduksjon skal tas hensyn til i arealplanlegging. De gir ogs\u00e5 uttalelse om kryssinger av vassdrag og vannledninger, og understreker at kommunen har ansvaret for \u00e5 ta hensyn til flom- og skredfare i arealplaner, uavhengig av NVEs r\u00e5d.The document is a statement regarding the establishment of the ski resort \"Arctic Center\" in Troms\u00f8 municipality. It mentions the presence of 46 automatically protected Sami cultural heritage sites in the area, one of which is a hearth dating back to the 18th-19th centuries. These cultural heritage sites are considered important for the Sami reindeer herding history and are automatically protected under the Cultural Heritage Act. The document highlights the significance of the R\u00e1vdnjev\u00e1ggi/Finnheia area as a national cultural heritage site and raises concerns about the impact of the proposed development on the Sami cultural history and lifestyle in the region.\n\nSametinget uttrykker bekymring for at et planlagt tiltak kan skade et automatisk fredet samisk kulturminne, og understreker at tillatelse m\u00e5 s\u00f8kes for inngrep i slike kulturminner. De p\u00e5peker ogs\u00e5 at planforslaget kan komme i konflikt med reindriftsloven og oppfordrer til konsultasjoner med ber\u00f8rte samiske interesser. Sametinget gir ingen merknader til visse omr\u00e5der i planen, men har innsigelser mot andre omr\u00e5der og h\u00e5per p\u00e5 god veiledning og oppf\u00f8lging for \u00e5 minimere skade.A preliminary response to a building permit application for the construction of a ski center in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn has been provided by the Troms\u00f8 municipality. The application must address various documents and requirements related to water supply, waste management, and other regulatory standards before further consideration. The municipality is seeking input from relevant authorities and may delegate decision-making power to the City and Urban Development Committee due to the project's scope and specific requirements. Failure to obtain the necessary dispensations may result in adherence to current zoning regulations or a revision of the zoning plan. The applicant is advised to ensure the application is complete and well-documented before the case can be reviewed for potential political approval.Anders Koller Tufte from Ihuga AS is following up on discussions regarding the Arctic Center and the application for a new access road. He mentions that a separate application will be submitted for this purpose.Anders Koller Tufte is responding to a letter from the Sametinget regarding the Arctic Center building case. Attached are responses to the letter.The application is for a building permit under the planning and building law for the property located at Straumsvegen 411, 9109 Kval\u00f8ya in Troms\u00f8. The proposed project is for a new non-residential building over 70 m2, specifically an indoor sports hall for leisure and tourism purposes. The applicant is Arctic Center AS, with Erik Joachimsen as the contact person.\n\nThe document contains information about a construction project, including contact details, responsible parties, application for dispensation, current plans, site location considerations, water supply, drainage, and miscellaneous attachments. It also includes a declaration of responsibility for the project and the necessary expertise, along with relevant documentation.\"Risten Turi Aleksandersen\" is requesting a meeting with the municipality regarding the Finnheia alpine village. They have been preoccupied with a wind power project and have not been able to follow up on this matter. They are requesting a meeting before the deadline for complaints expires to discuss and present their views on the issue.\"Benn Molund is requesting clarification on why his comments on a neighbor notification were not included in the post list to the Troms\u00f8 municipality. He had previously raised concerns about a proposed construction project and outlined various issues, including the impact on his properties, the need for a new regulatory plan, and the lack of response from the recipients. There are ongoing discussions and requests for further information and clarification.The email exchanges involve discussions about supplementing a permit application with requested documentation, particularly related to construction projects and environmental regulations. There is also mention of potential issues with obtaining dispensations and clarifications on the planned infrastructure. The sender requests feedback on a draft meeting summary before publication.The email is from Ronald M. J\u00f8rgensen to Thea Solvoll Liahjell regarding a previous phone call about the establishment of the \"Arctic Center\" ski resort. Ronald clarifies that a horizontal boring method will be used for the water pipeline instead of traditional digging. He requests a meeting to discuss this method and its impact on the cultural heritage in the area. He also mentions contacting the Sami Parliament and provides a copy of a previous note sent to them. He is awaiting a response from Thea.Benn Molund has objections to a construction project and requests a new regulatory plan be approved. He raises concerns about the impact of the development on his properties, including environmental impacts, infrastructure issues, and restrictions on further development. Anders Koller Tufte agrees to look into the matter and provide more information.Hilgunn Angvik is forwarding a message regarding a permit application for the Arctic Center that incorrectly states that water supply will not cross another property. She received a neighbor notification about a water pipeline near her property without mention of unstable ground and is requesting that the permit not be approved until the water issue is resolved.Ina Ulrikke Rasmussen apologized for not responding earlier to Geir Johnsen's inquiry regarding the building application. She explained that no new documents have been received in the case since May 27, 2022, and further documentation is needed for the application to be processed. Geir Johnsen had raised concerns about a water and sewage plan for Arctic Center AS, but had not received a response from the municipality despite multiple attempts. He questioned the handling of the consultation process and raised various issues related to potential impacts on his property's water supply.IHUGA AS has received a notice of a fee for their building application in Troms\u00f8, as the processing time has exceeded the norm by a significant amount. The fee will be based on the actual time spent on the application, which is currently around 60 hours. The municipality cannot determine the total processing time at this point, as it depends on various factors. The letter is signed by Anne-Marte T\u00f8gersen and Thea Solvoll Liahjell from the Section for Urban Development and Building Applications.Anders Koller Tufte sent an email to Thea Solvoll Liahjell regarding the subject \"AC\" with multiple attachments related to a project. Anders is the Faglig Leder at ihuga.no and can be contacted at anders@ihuga.no or +47 40455721. The email includes various attachments such as P1933_0-0-005_B04.pdf, Vannledning.docx, L200.1.pdf, L201.2.pdf, and 230705 Svarbrev Sametinget dispensasjonss\u00f8knad vannledning.pdf.Siljan Mari Viken from Troms\u00f8 kommune is objecting to the establishment of a ski resort in H\u00e5k\u00f8ybotn, Arctic Center. She believes that the project has not been thoroughly assessed for its environmental and social impacts. She argues that the current plans are outdated and incomplete, and calls for a new, independent impact assessment that takes into account all stages of the project. She also questions the sustainability and necessity of the resort, stating that tourists come to the area for its natural beauty and tranquility, not for artificial ski slopes. Viken expresses concerns about the potential negative effects on the local environment and economy, and urges decision-makers to consider the long-term consequences before approving the project.Anders Koller Tufte requested a meeting regarding the Arctic Center construction, but Thea Solvoll Liahjell informed him via email that they could not hold the meeting on Friday. Instead, they will send a letter with responses to the questions that were to be addressed at the meeting. The letter may not be sent before the following Tuesday. Liahjell will be absent for the next four weeks, so communication during that time should be directed to unit leader Anne-Marte T\u00f8gersen.Karianne Laagstein is asking Thea Solvoll Liahjell for information on the status of the Arctic Center project and when a final response is expected on the application for a building permit. Thea apologizes for documents not being available on the portal and provides Karianne with the necessary documents.Anders Koller Tufte from Ihuga AS emails Thea Solvoll Liahjell from Troms\u00f8 kommune, requesting the timesheet for saksbehandlingsgebyr. Thea replies with the timesheet attached in the email.Ronald M. J\u00f8rgensen is responding to Thea Solvoll Liahjell's request for a statement regarding the establishment of the \"Arctic Center\" ski resort. He clarifies that the water pipeline will not be dug traditionally, but will instead use horizontal drilling to minimize impact on the terrain. J\u00f8rgensen requests a meeting to discuss the construction method and its relationship to the cultural heritage in the area, noting that the Sami Parliament has been involved in the decision-making process. He also includes a note sent to the Sami Parliament for reference.Statsforvalteren i Troms og Finnmark har mottatt en klage fra Troms\u00f8 kommune ang\u00e5ende en rammetillatelse og dispensasjon for oppf\u00f8ring av naust p\u00e5 en eiendom. Etter \u00e5 ha vurdert saken, har Statsforvalteren besluttet \u00e5 oppheve vedtaket p\u00e5 grunn av manglende oversendelse av s\u00f8knaden om dispensasjon til ber\u00f8rte sektormyndigheter, noe som utgj\u00f8r en saksbehandlingsfeil. Klagen har derfor blitt tatt til f\u00f8lge, og saken blir sendt tilbake til kommunen for ny vurdering. Statsforvalteren vil gi en n\u00e6rmere begrunnelse for avgj\u00f8relsen i etterkant.\n\nStatsforvalteren har mottatt dokumenter ang\u00e5ende en s\u00f8knad om dispensasjon for oppf\u00f8ring av en naustbygning p\u00e5 60m2 over to etasjer, som ble avsl\u00e5tt av kommunen. Statsforvalteren hadde tidligere anbefalt at dispensasjon ikke ble gitt. Etter at en ny s\u00f8knad om rammetillatelse og dispensasjon ble inngitt med en reduksjon til kun en etasje, ble denne s\u00f8knaden innvilget av kommunen den 6. april 2022.\n\nEn dispensasjonss\u00f8knad for et byggeprosjekt ble innvilget av kommunen uten at den reviderte s\u00f8knaden ble oversendt til ber\u00f8rte sektormyndigheter for uttalelse. Tre eiere av eiendommen har sammen p\u00e5klaget vedtaket, deres klage gjelder dispensasjon fra byggegrensen mot sj\u00f8. Eierne har engasjert en advokatfullmektig for bistand i saken, som har inngitt supplerende merknader til klagesaksbehandlingen.\n\nAdvokatfullmektig Falck har i sitt brev p\u00e5pekt at klagen ble inngitt rettidig og at tiltaket ikke n\u00f8dvendigvis vil v\u00e6re avhengig av dispensasjon. Kommunen behandlet klagen og mente den ikke kunne tas til f\u00f8lge, men konkluderte samtidig med at klagen var inngitt rettidig. Saken ble sendt til Statsforvalteren for endelig avgj\u00f8relse. Statsforvalteren har vurdert at klagen ble fremsatt rettidig av parter med klageinteresse og vil vurdere alle sider av saken, inkludert nye omstendigheter og anf\u00f8rsler fremsatt av klagerne.\n\nStatsforvalteren skal legge stor vekt p\u00e5 hensynet til det kommunale selvstyret n\u00e5r de er klageinstans for vedtak truffet av en kommune. I denne konkrete saken gjelder det klage over vedtak om rammetillatelse og dispensasjon for oppf\u00f8ring av naustbygning i Troms\u00f8 kommune. Tiltaket m\u00e5 v\u00e6re i tr\u00e5d med lov, forskrift og plan, og eiendommen er omfattet av tre ulike planer, deriblant kommuneplanens arealdel og en gjeldende reguleringsplan.\n\nThe property in question is covered by the municipal plan for Sommar\u00f8y, Hilles\u00f8y, and Brensholmen with plan ID 0252, adopted on September 26, 2018. The property is marked on the map with light green color with diagonal lines within the H510_30 area, designated for agriculture, nature, outdoor activities, and reindeer husbandry. According to planning regulations, in case of conflict, the newest plan takes precedence over older ones. In this case, the municipal plan supersedes any previous zoning or development plans.\n\nPlanen gjelder med unntak av endringer knyttet til bebyggelse, samferdsel, gr\u00f8nnstruktur, sj\u00f8 og vassdrag, forsvar og hensynssoner. Kommunedelplanen g\u00e5r foran reguleringsplanen ved motstrid, men reguleringsplanen gjelder fortsatt med mindre det er angitt noe annet. I en bestemmelse i reguleringsplanen ang\u00e5ende landbruksomr\u00e5der st\u00e5r det at naust kan oppf\u00f8res i tilknytning til hytte- og/eller boligbebyggelse, uten krav om dispensasjon s\u00e5 lenge det skjer i forbindelse med eksisterende bebyggelse. Statsforvalteren er enig i tolkningen om at naust kan tillates oppf\u00f8rt i denne sammenheng.\n\nThe provision regarding the construction of boathouses in the area may not be clear enough to serve as a basis for development, according to both the municipality and the speaker. However, a definitive decision on this issue has not been made, as the municipal sub-plan for Sommar\u00f8y, Hilles\u00f8y, and Brensholmen is considered to take precedence over the regulation plan's provision. The sub-plan emphasizes the importance of preserving agricultural land and prohibits further fragmentation of farmland. Additionally, the sub-plan designates certain areas for agriculture, nature, outdoor recreation, and reindeer husbandry, allowing for the construction of buildings related to agriculture. This conflicts with the regulation plan's allowance for boathouses in the area for residential and holiday homes.\n\nKommunedelplanen skjerper landbrukshensynene i omr\u00e5det ved \u00e5 kreve at bygninger i landbruksomr\u00e5der m\u00e5 v\u00e6re tilknyttet landbruksdrift. En s\u00f8knad om \u00e5 bygge et naust for fritidsbebyggelse krever derfor dispensasjon. Kommunen begikk en saksbehandlingsfeil ved ikke \u00e5 sende dispensasjonss\u00f8knaden til ber\u00f8rte myndigheter for uttalelse f\u00f8r de innvilget den. Derfor har Statsforvalteren opphevet kommunens vedtak og returnert saken for fornyet behandling."